Description: West Freeway Church of Christ shooting: Two people were killed inside the West Freeway Church of Christ by a gunman before he was shot and killed by a member of the security team. The attack was livestreamed, leading to numerous social media posts showing the shooting in progress.
A dispute began at a rented Airbnb during a New Year's Eve party. Three men were killed and another man and woman were wounded.
A shooting unfolded outside a nightclub on New Year's Eve that killed a man and sent three others to the hospital.
An adult and three juveniles were wounded in an evening shooting.
Four people were injured in a drive-by shooting shortly before midnight.
Five people were shot outside a home after returning from a bar in Modesto where they had been involved in an altercation.
One person was killed and three people were wounded in a shooting at an afterhours club.
Four people were wounded after a shooting at a party. All four are expected to survive.
Six shoppers were wounded at a grocery supermarket by two shooters.
Three people were killed and two others wounded in a shooting during the early morning.
Five women aged 18 to 32 years old were injured by gunfire after the home they were in was shot at by an unknown person.
A gunman shot and killed his girlfriend, her two children, and her mother. He was arrested after exchanging fire with police and attempting to carjack a vehicle.
Four men were wounded after a shooting near a restaurant.
During an outdoor New Year's Eve party, a physical fight started escalated to a shooting, with multiple people firing guns.
Two people were killed and two others injured in a shooting outside a nightclub.
After an argument escalated on a front porch, four people were wounded by gunfire, with one man dying later at the hospital.
Three people were killed and two others were wounded in a shooting outside of a bar.
Six people were wounded in an evening shooting. One of the victims later died at the hospital.
Six shooters opened fire on a busy street with six wounded.
2022 Chattanooga shooting: Fourteen were shot, two of them fatally, at a nightclub during the early morning. A third person was killed by a vehicle attempting to flee.
Two people were killed and seven injured in a drive-by shooting at a music video set.
Seven people were wounded during a shooting at a holiday party.

Don Carter Lanes shooting: Three people are killed and three others injured in a shooting at a bowling alley. The shooter is believed to have selected his victims at random. A person of interest has been taken into custody by authorities.
An adult and infant were killed and two adults wounded in an afternoon shooting.
One person was killed and three others injured in an early morning shooting at the Festival of the Arts.
Officers responding to a call about an individual shot arrived at a house party and found four teenagers injured.
Four people were wounded during a shooting at a holiday party.
Two men were killed and two injured in an early morning targeted shooting in Ybor City.
A man was killed and three others wounded at a local gas station.

Eight people, including six children, were shot during a graduation party after occupants in two cars opened fire at the partygoers in the yard of the house it was being held at. An adult woman was killed.
Officers responding to a call of suspicious circumstances near an intersection found one man killed and two others and a woman injured.
Five people were injured in a shooting outside a deli.
Three adults and a juvenile were wounded in an afternoon drive-by shooting. One of the wounded later died at the hospital.
A gunman went on a shooting spree across multiple locations in the Denver metropolitan area before dying in a shootout with police.
2022 Philadelphia shooting: Fourteen people were shot, three of them fatally, by multiple shooters on South Street. One of the shooters may have been shot by a responding police officer.

Five people were wounded by gunfire outside a night club, with an additional three injured by the resulting building damage and chaos. The shooting occurred after an altercation escalated out onto the street.
Five people were wounded in a shooting.
Four people were injured and one was killed after a shooting on Christmas Day.
A man was killed and three others were wounded at a local apartment complex.
A teenager was fatally shot, and three others were wounded.
Police responding to reports of shots fired discovered four wounded victims, one of which died later at the hospital.
One person was killed and three others were injured in a shooting near the Colorado Springs Airport.
Five females aged between eight and fifty; three were children, were found killed by a family member. Police believe it was domestic related.
Four adults were wounded inside a pop-up store.
A couple was arrested after the boyfriend shot three people during an argument. The boyfriend was also shot.
One person was killed and three injured in a shooting outside a bar, after an earlier argument in a restaurant.
Four men were injured in a shooting that occurred inside a barbershop. The suspect evaded police but the weapon was recovered.
After a teenager got into a conflict with another group, four people were injured and one was killed after a shooting at the teenager's home.
Four people were wounded at a rest stop, and the shooter fled before police arrived. The shooter was later found dead.
Four people were shot, one fatally, at an abandoned home.
Four people wounded by gunfire were discovered by police after responding to a house party.
One person was killed and three others were wounded in a shooting just before midnight.
Four individuals were discovered killed in three separate homes after wellness checks were called for them. The perpetrator died of a self inflicted gunshot wound.
Three teenagers were killed and a fourth wounded in a convenience store.
Five teenagers were wounded in a targeted shooting at an early morning graduation house party after two groups at the party began fighting.
Six people were wounded in a shooting in which the perpetrator was believed to have exited a vehicle and opened fire before leaving in it.
Four people were injured by gunfire inside a strip club following a fight. One additional person was stabbed.
A wife, husband, and two children were fatally shot inside of their home.
Seven people were wounded at a party in the early morning. An 18-year-old was later arrested.
A fight during a party being held at a strip mall escalated into gunfire, with nine people being shot.
Shooters wearing ski masks exited a vehicle and wounded four people before fleeing.
One person was killed and three others were wounded in a shooting.
Two men were killed at a sports bar in an apparent targeted shooting. Two innocent bystanders were wounded.
Four people were wounded in a drive by shooting in North Philadelphia.
Four people were shot, one fatally, shortly before midnight near an apartment complex.
Thirteen people were shot at a party that was held to memorialize a victim of an earlier shooting, at least one was a teenager.
Five people were wounded outside of a nightclub in Queens after a dispute inside the club.
Six people were wounded after someone walked into and opened fire inside a South Side beauty salon in the Burnside neighborhood, shortly after midnight. The salon was hosting an after hours party.
Four people were wounded near a Waffle House in the early morning.
Six people were shot, one fatally, during a party. One of the shooting victims also suffered a broken arm.
Seven people were wounded in an early morning shooting, including two 17-year-olds.
Five people were wounded in a shooting in the Overtown neighborhood of Miami.
Three men and a woman were shot in the Kingsessing neighborhood.  Cocaine and firearms were recovered on the scene.
Four men were wounded outside a Brooklyn deli shortly before midnight.

Two police officers responding to a domestic disturbance were fired upon by two men. In the ensuing gun battle, a shooter and a police officer were killed. The surviving officer and shooter were both shot.
One person was killed and six injured in an apartment complex after a drive-by shooting.
Four people were wounded in a shooting. Two suspects were taken into custody by police.
Following a dispute outside of a restaurant four were people shot.
A woman was arrested after killing one and wounding three in a domestic incident at an apartment.
Warren Clinic shooting: At least four people were killed and multiple were injured after a shooting inside a building on the Saint Francis Hospital campus. The shooter fatally shot himself.
Two people were killed and a police officer and bystander injured at the local Sanitation Department after a fight escalated.
A thirteen-year-old boy was killed and six other people were injured in a shooting at a block party. At least two shooters were involved, and police believe it may have been gang-related.
A family member discovered two parents and two children, aged 12 and 13-years-old, killed in their home. The killer was reportedly a third teenaged child of the family.
Six people were found wounded in a local home, with one identified as the potential shooter.
Four people were shot in the Carver neighborhood.
Two people were killed and two were injured in a late night double homicide.
Two people were killed and two others were wounded in a shooting at an intersection.
A man was killed and three others wounded in an early morning shooting.
One man was killed and three others were wounded in a shooting across the street from a strip club.

A concerned relative checked their family at their home and found four of them dead. A man had killed his girlfriend and her two eldest children before committing suicide. Three younger children were found unharmed in the home.
A resident at Babcock Village Apartments shot two employees, one fatally, and one resident before killing himself.
Four people were wounded in a drive-by shooting while attending a vigil for a resident of their area who had died of natural causes.
A man was killed and three others were wounded inside a deli.
One person was killed and three wounded in Upton.
Ten people were shot during a party in a vacant parking lot, including a teenager. A police officer who was arriving at the scene was shot at in his police cruiser and suffered a shrapnel injury.
Four people were shot at the South Park Mall.
Two people were killed and two others were wounded in a shooting outside a pizza shop. A suspect was taken into custody by police.
Four men were wounded in an afternoon shooting in the Boerum Hill neighborhood of Brooklyn.
Four adults were wounded in the early morning at a gentleman's club.
A shooting at a party in the Port Richmond neighborhood left two dead, including a teenager, and two others wounded.
Three people are killed and one wounded in a shooting at the Emerald City Casino. The suspect was later killed by police at a different location.
Two people were killed and five others were wounded in a shooting outside of a convenience store. Two of the injured were hit with bullets, the other three were injured in other ways.
A man was killed and three others wounded at a large early morning gathering.
A man was killed and four people wounded in Penn North.
Seven people were shot, one fatally, outside a bar and a liquor store during the early morning.
One man was killed and four others injured at an intersection early in the morning.
Three people were killed and two others were injured in a home invasion shooting. One person was arrested the next day, and police suspect another person was involved.
Four people were wounded near the Charles Spencer Elementary School during school hours. No students were harmed or in danger.
Four people were wounded in an afternoon shooting.
Four people were shot in the Willow Springs neighborhood. A victim driving away from the scene fatally struck a motorcyclist.
Four teenagers were wounded in a drive-by shooting at an apartment complex.
Four people were injured in a shooting in the Penrose neighborhood of St. Louis.
Five men were wounded in a late night shooting. They were playing dice outside an apartment complex when a man drove up and started shooting. The man chased them through the complex before fleeing.
Police were alerted to four wounded by gunfire after an argument escalated through a shotspotter alert.
A man shot four people, one fatally, at a home in the Humboldt Park neighborhood before barricading himself inside during a domestic-related incident. The shooter was eventually shot by a SWAT team.
One man was killed and three wounded in a business parking lot.
One person was killed and three others were injured in a shooting in the LoDo neighborhood.
Two people were killed and two wounded in a parking lot after an SUV pulled into it.
Four adults were wounded in Kengsington, they were found by patrolling police.
One person was killed and seven others wounded after a shooting at a Memorial Day festival at the Old City Square.

2019 Jersey City shooting: Four people were killed, including a police officer, and another three were injured in an ambush style shootout by a man and woman who were killed by police. The suspects were Black Hebrew Israelites members and targeted a kosher grocery store.
Four people were discovered shot execution style in the head in a basement of a home.

A group of four men attempted to rob a home at gun point. The home owner opened fire in defense and killed two of the robbers and wounded the other two. The homeowner's four-year-old child was also wounded.
Six people in an SUV were shot at in the early morning, causing the SUV to crash. Two adults were killed and four juveniles wounded.
Seven people were shot on U.S. Route 95, causing the highway to be shut down in both directions for several hours.
Four people were discovered dead in a home, in either by a murder-suicide or a quadruple homicide. A toddler was also in the home, unharmed.

Mercy Hospital shooting: A gunman opened fire in the Mercy Hospital and Medical Center in Chicago, killing a doctor at the hospital who was his former fiancée, a police officer, and one other person before being killed either by himself or by police.
Six people were wounded at a rodeo outdoor live music venue, with one to two thousand attendees present. Police had been called to the venue three times prior to the shooting, due to fights.
Six people were wounded at local sports bar in the early morning.
Six people were shot during a house party.
Two men were killed and three injured at an apartment building. The incident was originally reported as a home invasion, although the account was not confirmed.

A man killed his girlfriend and wounded his uncle and grandmother in a shooting in Watts, Los Angeles. The shooter was also injured, either during a confrontation with police or by a self-inflicted gunshot.
Officers responding to reports of a shooting shortly after midnight found a woman dead and three other individuals injured.
Five people were wounded in the early morning, a suspect was arrested days later.
Four people were shot, one fatally, at a house party during the early morning.
Five people were shot outside a local bar, with one man dying of his injuries at the hospital.
Police found a boy suffering from gunshot injuries, then discovered a car that had crashed into a ditch. Inside the car were three people who had all been shot and killed.
Shortly before midnight an argument between two men at a bonfire escalated. Six people were wounded.
One person was killed and fourteen others wounded in a drive-by shooting at a memorial vigil in Baytown for another shooting victim.
Five people, including a teenager, were shot in the West Garfield Park neighborhood in the early morning.

Naval Air Station Pensacola shooting: A man killed three individuals and injured eight more at Naval Air Station Pensacola before being killed by police. A terrorist motive is suspected to be behind the attack.
Two people were shot inside a home, and two others were shot at a gas station. One of the victims later died of their injuries.
Three men and a seventeen-year-old girl were injured after someone shot at them from across the street. The group was standing outside a home in West Garfield Park.
Three security guards and a bystander were shot by a gunman at a nightclub.
Four people were shot during an illegal car show between the Hollywood and Hyde Park neighborhoods.

2019 Miramar shootout: Four people are dead and one injured after a pair of men rob a jewelry store in Coral Gables, injuring the clerk, then carjack a UPS truck and lead police on a chase that ended in a shootout in Miramar that killed the UPS driver, a bystander, and the suspects.
Three people were killed and one person was injured in a shooting.
An eighteen-year-old was killed and three other teenagers were injured after a dispute between two groups escalated.
Four adults were shot at a bowling alley at approximately 1 AM, killing a 23-year-old man.
A disturbance between two teenagers at a house party escalated into a shooting that wounded four after one of the teenagers opened fire shortly before midnight.

22-year-old Gabriel Romero, a US Navy sailor and submarine crewman, randomly opened fire just minutes after starting his shift for routine guard duty at at Joint Base Pearl Harbor–Hickam. He opened fire on a group of civilian workers, killing two and wounded another, before immediately shooting himself. The motive is thought to be a toxic cultural environment in the USN, particularly among submarine crewman.
A man killed two people and wounded two others after shooting them during what police believe to be a drug robbery. One of the deceased men is suspected to have been the perpetrator.
A man was killed, and shortly later a woman and two children; aged 10 and 7-years-old were killed at a home. An additional child was found uninjured in the home.
Three teenagers and a baby were shot while in a car near an intersection, killing a 17-year-old girl.
One teenager was killed and three were wounded in a shooting in the McLane neighborhood.
Two people were killed and two wounded in an apartment complex.
A person killed three people and injured a fourth before killing themself in a residence in an apparent murder–suicide.
Eleven people were shot at a motorcycle club. The injured were treated at nearby hospitals and no arrests have been made.
Five people were shot in a drive-by shooting in the Callahan neighborhood.
Six people were injured during an exchange of gunfire in the Riverfront neighborhood.
One person was killed and three police officers wounded when a home invasion turned into a hostage situation.
A man killed three people and injured one in a shooting after a fight at a home. The shooter was arrested after crashing a vehicle he stole from the scene.
Two people were killed and two wounded in an apartment complex near Memphis International Airport.
Five people were shot in the Grier Heights neighborhood.
Four people were shot, one fatally, in a shooting in a bar parking lot during the early morning hours.
One woman was killed and three others wounded, including a perpetrator, after an argument escalated at a nightclub.
Three people were killed and one injured when a man began firing at 5 individuals at a bar following a pool game. The suspect was arrested.
Four people were shot in the evening, in New Orleans East.
Responding officers found one person killed and two wounded, with an additional two wounded found at the hospital.
A man fatally shot his wife and his step-children before non-fatally shooting himself in the head.
Two people were killed and two injured at an intersection hours after the first mass shooting in the city.

Shooting of Jemel Roberson: A man re-entered a bar after being ejected and began to fire, wounding three people and becoming injured himself. Armed security guards apprehended the suspect. Responding officers saw one of the security guards with a gun, and shot and killed him.
A man was killed and fourteen other people were injured shortly after midnight at a nightclub. At least three men fled in a vehicle and continued to fire from the vehicle.
Three men and a teenager were wounded in Brewerytown.
Six people, including several teenagers, were shot at a graduation party.
One person was killed and four were injured in a shooting in Aurora, Illinois.
Two people were killed and four people were wounded when they were shot after an argument over gambling.
A woman was killed and five people wounded by gunfire and two stabbed outside a nightclub after an early morning argument.
Four men were shot by a gunman, two of whom succumbed to their injuries.
Four people were shot, including two teenagers, while on the way to a prom party in the Mantua neighborhood.
2019 New Orleans shooting: Ten people were shot in a densely populated area with heavy police presence at a time when tens of thousands of tourists were downtown for the Bayou Classic football game.

Thousand Oaks shooting: A man entered a bar hosting a student line-dancing event and killed twelve people, including a police officer. Sixteen other people were injured, one of them by gunfire. The gunman then killed himself.
Five people were wounded while leaving a club in the early morning. A sixth person was wounded by a stray bullet while at home.

A fight broke out in the parking lot of a bar, after a group was ejected. It escalated, with bystanders attempting to intervene. A man walked up and shot at the bystanders killing one and wounding three.

Robb Elementary School shooting: An 18-year-old shot his grandmother at their home before driving to Robb Elementary School, where he entered the school unobstructed, barricading himself inside a classroom and fatally shooting twenty-one people, including nineteen children. Eighteen people in total were wounded. The shooter was eventually fatally shot by a Border Patrol officer, which was shot during the shootout.
Seven people were shot at a nightclub in the early morning.
Five people were wounded in a shooting outside of a nightclub. The suspect was taken into custody by police.
One person was killed and four injured in a shooting outside a 7-Eleven store. The possible suspects were arrested on other charges in nearby Parker, Arizona.
Two teenagers were killed and a teenager and an infant were wounded in a drive-by shooting at a gas station.
Five people were shot during a memorial service in the Collinwood neighborhood.
Five people were wounded including two children aged 10 and 15.
Four people were injured in a shooting in North Long Beach. Police suspect the incident was gang-related.
Four people were wounded in an evening shooting in the Stuyvesant area.
Responding officers found two adults and a child killed and three adults wounded.
Five people were injured in an early morning shooting at a nightclub. Several others were injured by broken glass during the chaos of the shooting.
Two men were killed and two others wounded in a drive-by shooting. One suspect was arrested after the car crashed into a parked police car.
2018 Tallahassee shooting: A gunman killed two women and injured five others; four by gunfire, one by being pistol-whipped, at a yoga studio before killing himself in a murder–suicide.
A woman was killed and six others were injured at a party in the Bedford–Stuyvesant neighborhood of Brooklyn.

Oxford High School shooting: A 15-year-old student opened fire at Oxford High School initially killing three students and wounding seven others and a teacher, before being arrested. One of the wounded died a day later. The suspect was charged with four counts of murder and seven counts of attempted murder while his parents, who bought him the gun used in the shooting as an early Christmas present, were charged with four counts of involuntary manslaughter.
Police discovered five people shot to death at a public housing complex in the Caimito barrio.
Six people were wounded at a warehouse party after an argument escalated and the perpetrator opened fire.
An argument evolved into a shooting that left five people wounded.
Six people were wounded in an early morning shooting in Gresham on the South Side after a man opened fire on them from the sidewalk.

Responding officers to a domestic incident were shot at by the suspect. The suspect had killed two women and wounded a child previously. An officer and the suspect were killed and another officer was wounded.
A man fatally shot his two teenage daughters and his wife before shooting himself.
Two people were killed and two others injured in an early morning shooting at a club.
Two men were killed and two other people were wounded in a shooting at a home.
A woman was killed and three adults and a teenager were wounded at an illegal warehouse party.
Responding police found six adults and a teenager wounded in East Baltimore.
A drive-by shooting in the South End area left four wounded.
One person was killed and four others injured in a drive-by shooting after being made to leave a club following an argument.
A fifteen-year-old boy was killed and three other people were wounded in a shooting at a home after a robbery.
Two people were killed and two others wounded at a Sonic Drive-In after police responded to a call of a bomb inside a truck. A suspect has been arrested.
A teenager was killed and four others wounded at a gas station.
A shooting occurred at a home, leaving two people dead and three injured.
One person was killed and six injured after an argument at a club escalated and the perpetrator began to fire randomly.
Two people were killed and three others were wounded in a shooting.

A family of four, a husband and wife and their two adult sons, were shot in their home. The husband is in critical condition at a local hospital. A recently discharged gun was found at the scene and police do not believe there is a suspect at large.
A man killed his four children and his mother in law in their home. He turned himself in to police an hour later and was charged with five counts of murder.
A shooting occurred at an after-prom party, leaving one dead and nine injured.
Four people were wounded at an outdoor party after a fight broke out.
Five people were injured in a drive-by shooting in South Los Angeles.

Mayfair Mall shooting: Eight people were hospitalized with non-life-threatening injuries after a person opened fire at the Mayfair Mall. Several people, including a 15-year-old boy from Milwaukee, have been arrested in the case.
Five youths were wounded in a shooting.
Four people were shot, one fatally, in the Holy Cross neighborhood.
Five people were wounded randomly as a man drove down a road and opened fire on pedestrians.
Seven people were wounded in a shooting following a fight at a nightclub.
One person was killed and three injured in a drive-by shooting while standing under a carport.
Four people were wounded in an evening shooting in Kingsessing.
A drive-by shooting in front of a grocery store wounded three and killed one.
Four people were wounded in an apartment complex during a large gathering.
Two people were killed and two were injured in a shooting at a home.
A man shot and killed his uncle and cousin and wounded his wife and aunt before committing suicide. His uninjured infant daughter was also in the home.
A teenager was killed and three others were wounded after men in a car opened fire in the South Ward.

Magnificent Mile shooting: An individual opened fire during an altercation between two groups of teenagers, killing two and injuring eight. The shooter engaged in a chase with police in the subway, during which a woman fell onto the train tracks and was electrocuted during the chaos.
Four people were wounded in a shooting.

Pittsburgh synagogue shooting: A man opened fire in the Tree of Life synagogue in an antisemitic attack, killing eleven people and injuring six others (including four police officers). The suspect was taken into custody by police.
Four people were wounded in an evening shooting.
Home invaders killed two teenagers and wounded their mother, two teenage siblings and an adult sibling. One of the assailants was also killed.
An estranged husband opened fire on his wife, killing her, their daughter, and his mother-in-law before committing suicide.
One person was killed and three people were injured in two homes on one street.
Five people were wounded by several shooters at a high school Halloween party.
Four people were wounded at a home that had been the site of a break in back in January 2020.
Two men were killed and two others wounded in a believed targeted drive-by shooting. Eyewitnesses are not cooperating with police.
Five people were shot in the Cecil B. Moore neighborhood, including a teenager.
2019 Fresno shooting: Ten people were shot, four fatally, at a football watch party.
A seventeen-year-old was killed and three other people were wounded in a shooting.
Two adults and two children under the age of seven were wounded in a drive-by shooting. They were standing outside a home in Golden Glades.
Four people were wounded and transported to the hospital in private vehicles.
Four people were shot, one of them fatally, at a park in a targeted attack.
Four people were wounded outside a home by a drive-by shooting.
Several gunmen wounded five people who were standing on a sidewalk.
Four people were wounded in a drive-by shooting while walking down a road on the West Side. Two of the wounded were teenage girls.
Four people were wounded after a large party was ending. Police believe it connected to another incident near a local hospital.
Seven people were shot in three connected shootings that preceded an exchange of gunfire.
A man killed his estranged wife and their three children, wounding a fourth child, before killing himself.
Six people were injured at a funeral service for Vantrease Criss, a rapper who was killed a week before.
Four people were wounded at the Dearborn homes after another group began an argument which escalated.
A man was killed and three others wounded shortly before noon. A suspect was arrested.
Two teenagers and two juveniles were shot at a house in the Shepard Street–South Road Street Historic District.
Saugus High School shooting: A high school student shot five classmates, two fatally, before shooting himself; he died the next day in the hospital.
Six people were injured in a drive-by shooting before an NFL game between the Houston Texans and the Jacksonville Jaguars. Those injured were between the ages of 20 and 70.
Five people were shot shortly after midnight while attending a street gathering.
Two men were killed and two juveniles were wounded while in a vehicle outside an apartment complex.
2022 Laguna Woods shooting: A man motivated by anti-Taiwanese sentiment opened fire at a church, killing one and wounding five others, before being physically restrained by churchgoers.
Four people were shot randomly along a road.
One person was killed and three were wounded after three gunmen began shooting at a nightclub following an argument.
Two men were killed and two injured at a trailer park in a late night shooting.
A man was killed and four others were wounded in the parking lots of a local club.
Two people were killed, and three others were injured, at a flea market after an argument escalated into a shooting in the Meadowviewland neighborhood.
Four people were wounded outside a night club after a disturbance escalated.
Four people were injured in a drive-by shooting.
Shortly before midnight, three people were killed and a pregnant woman wounded in a home.
Four adults and one child were shot during a backyard party.
Five people were shot at a nightclub in the morning, with one person dying.
A woman was killed and four others were wounded during an early morning shooting at a strip club.
A mother and four teenage children were found by an older brother in an apparent murder–suicide in which the mother is the reported perpetrator.
Four people were wounded in a late night shooting at an event center. The center had been rented out for a birthday party prior to the shooting.
Two men were killed and two wounded at an apartment complex.
2022 Buffalo shooting: An 18-year-old white supremacist clad in body armor opened fire at a Tops supermarket, killing ten, including a security guard, and wounding three others.
An adult male and three children, aged 12 through 13-years-old, were wounded by an unknown perpetrator while filming a rap music video.
Two children and two adults were injured in a drive-by shooting.
Four teenagers, aged between twelve and fifteen, were wounded in an evening drive by shooting in the Winton Hills area.
Four people were wounded at a local bar in the early morning.
A gunfight among several groups of people wounded seventeen people following an NBA game in the East Town neighborhood.
Two vehicles were shot at, wounding three adults and a 10-year-old child.
Two people were killed and two were injured in a shooting outside of a Halloween party.
Officers responding to an assault with a deadly weapon call found two men who later died at a hospital. Three additional wounded individuals were identified at a hospital.
One teen was killed, and three other teens were wounded in two separate but related shootings on the same block.
Two people were killed, and three were injured, in a shooting in the Deep Ellum neighborhood.
Four men were wounded in a drive-by shooting in a parking lot.
Three people were killed and one was wounded after someone arguing with them outside a shopping center shot them and fled.
Officers responding to reports of multiple gunshots found two men dead and four wounded in an evening shooting.
A man was killed and three others wounded in an afternoon shooting.
A fight outside a convention center following a high school graduation ceremony led to a shooting that injured four. No students or graduates were involved in the shooting or the fight.
An argument escalated and left one man injured and another dead. The shooter then engaged in a shootout with officers injuring two officers before being killed.
Four people were wounded near Glasgow Village when one or more people shot into a home.
Six people were shot, including two police officers, when an argument inside a nightclub escalated.
Two adults and two teens were wounded in a potentially targeted drive-by in Williamsbridge.
A teenage girl was killed, and four men wounded, in a shooting in the Sandy Hill neighborhood.
A man was killed and three other people were injured when a person opened fire at a group in a driveway.
A dispute at a one-year-olds birthday party, resulted in four men killed and one wounded.
A man was killed and seven other men and teenagers were wounded in a drive-by shooting. A car opened fire on a group gathered at a basketball court next to a Boys & Girls Club.
Four teens were shot during a gunfight near a high school.
Four people, including two children, were shot while they drove together in a vehicle in the West Englewood neighborhood.
Officers responding to a Shotspotter alert found four people wounded at a nightclub.
Six people were injured in a shooting at a fast food restaurant. One suspect was arrested and another turned himself in to police. A third person is also suspected of being involved.
Two adults and two children were wounded in an afternoon shooting at a local food mart. Police are investigating it as possible gang activity.
Four people were wounded in a drive-by shooting shortly after midnight on the Near West Side.
Four people, including a teenager and a baby, were injured in an ambush while they drove in a car in the Mark Twain neighborhood. One of the adult victims later succumbed to his injuries.
A man shot at five men working on a barn, killing one and injured three others.
Four people were wounded after being shot in central Las Vegas.
Two adults and two children under the age of twelve were wounded in a gated apartment complex.
Four men were shot outside of a bodega in Harlem.
Four people, including two teenagers, were shot along the Canal Walk after two groups of people began shooting at each other across the water following an argument.
One person was killed and five injured at an after hours party.
Four people were injured when a person in a vehicle fired shots at them at an apartment complex.
Eight people and a dog were injured in a shooting on Commerce Street in the early hours of the morning.
Six teenagers were wounded in a drive-by shooting at a park located across from a high school.
A shooter shot four people, one fatally, before fleeing and sparking a manhunt.
Four people were wounded in a shooting.
A man fired into a crowd outside a bar during a fight, injuring four people. Another person fired a gun into the air to try to stop the fight, but did not injure anyone.
Four men were wounded outside a local bar shortly before midnight.
Three men and three women were shot, one man critically.
Six people were shot by two men in a drive-by shooting in the Jackson Park neighborhood on the South Side.
Five teenagers were wounded at a Halloween party in a vacant home.
People began firing from a vehicle at people in a gas station parking lot, killing one person in a vehicle and wounding three others. The shooting is suspected to be gang-related.
One individual was killed and three injured inside a local bar shortly after midnight.
Two men opened fire at each other at a lounge, wounding five. One of the shooters was killed by responding police.
Five people were shot during a confrontation between two groups after at least one of the groups opened fire in northwestern Baltimore.
Four people were wounded in a drive-by shooting outside a night club.
Two men began shooting during a dispute, injuring six people in total including each other. Both men were arrested.
Two people were wounded and two killed in the Hollygrove section of the city. One of those killed may have been the target of the shooting.
Four people were shot, two of the victims fatally.  A man from Klamath Falls was arrested and charged with murder.
Five teenagers outside in the Back of the Yards neighborhood on the South Side were shot, one fatally, by multiple occupants of a stolen vehicle.
Orinda shooting: At an overnight Halloween party attended by over 100 people, five people were killed, and four more wounded by gunfire.

Several people began firing at teenagers in a car, killing one and wounding three. Police believe they were targeting people with whom they had been in a dispute on social media, and that the teenagers were mistakenly targeted. Seven suspects were arrested on various charges related to the shooting, including three people charged with first-degree murder.
Three people were killed and one injured near an apartment complex. The shooting is believed to be connected to a hit and run accident just down the road.
Four men arrived at a trailer park and confronted a homeowner and a guest, leading to the homeowner shooting and killing the four men and the guest being injured by the four attackers.
Four people were shot, one fatally, in the Milton-Montford neighborhood.
Three men were killed and nine injured at a Halloween party at a residential home.
Four people were wounded when they were injured in a gang-related shooting.
Four people were wounded in a shooting in a parking lot at a local sporting complex and gym located near the Jefferson City High School.
A man was killed and five others wounded at a gas station in the early morning.
Four people were shot, including two teenagers, in the Kensington neighborhood.
A man was killed and two adults and a 17-year-old were injured in front of a store.

Florence, South Carolina shooting: Officers were shot at during a two-hour standoff while attempting to execute a search warrant in which the perpetrator held children hostage, killing two and wounding six before being arrested.

A man shot and killed three people at an apartment complex before being shot dead by police. A fifth person was taken to a hospital with gunshot wounds but the condition of the person was not yet known.
Four people were wounded after several people opened fire at a party.
An argument in the common area of an apartment complex led to a shooting that injured five.
Four men were injured in a random drive by shooting.
One person was killed and four others were injured in a drive-by shooting outside of a store.
A man was killed and three wounded near a local bar that was hosting a Halloween party in the early morning.
Four people were wounded at a high school homecoming after-party, after multiple attendees began shooting.
A fight amongst a group of people in the Chandler Park neighborhood on the city's east side led to four people, including three teenagers, being shot.
One man was killed and four others were injured at a house party.
A man began firing a gun inside a vehicle, killing two passengers and wounding another passenger and the driver. He was arrested.
Six people were wounded in an early morning shooting at a party in an abandoned house.
Two children were killed and two adults wounded on the East End.
Three people were killed, and another three were injured, in a shooting at a condominium complex. The shooter has not been found.
Two men were killed and ten others injured at a large party to celebrate Texas A&M University's homecoming weekend.
A fight at an apartment complex, reportedly got out of control and three people were killed and two women wounded.
A man was killed and three others wounded shortly after midnight. A suspect was arrested shortly after.
Two wounded were found outside a vehicle, where two were found deceased in the backseat. Several weapons were found in the vehicle.
A shooting outside a house party left two teenagers dead, and two others injured, shortly before midnight.
Four people were wounded in a late night shooting.
Aberdeen, Maryland Shooting: An employee of the Rite Aid Distribution facility killed three victims before wounding herself. The shooter died later in the hospital.
Four people were wounded outside of a bar after an early morning argument escalated in a large crowd. The bar was the scene of a similar shooting in February 2019.
Four teenagers were wounded in an evening shooting.
A fight during an informal car meet among a group of people led to a shooting that injured four, including two juveniles.
Two people were killed and two injured at a home late at night.
A gunman opened fire in a municipal building and wounded four people before being shot by officer who responded to the incident.
A man was killed and three others injured after someone fired into an event center.
Three adults were killed and an adult and child were wounded after an argument escalated inside a home.
A shooting during the very early morning killed two, and wounded three.
One person was killed and three wounded at an apartment complex late at night.
A gunman opened fire at the WTS Paradigm software company and wounded three people. The gunman was injured in a shootout with the police, and later died in the hospital.
Two men were killed and two wounded outside an apartment building that was hosting a Halloween party, in the early morning.
A man was killed and three adults and a teenager wounded in an ambush-style shooting outside a grocery store.
A shooting in the Village de L'Est neighborhood left two killed, and four others wounded.
Four people were shot at random and wounded by a lone gunman.
A father shot and killed his wife and two children, and injured his adult stepdaughter, before he committed suicide.
Two men were killed and two wounded in the desert near Tucson International Airport in the early morning.
Three teenagers and an adult were wounded after three of them exited a local store in Feltonville and were chased down the street.

During a Cinco de Mayo festival, a gang member shot at a member of a rival gang who was in a crowd of people, wounding five bystanders--including four children. The shooting prompted the cancellation of the event. A 13-year old boy has now been arrested as the suspected shooter.
A woman was killed and three others injured in an early morning shooting.

A gunman opened fire at three locations after following a witness to another store and then to a private home. He killed two women and three men before carjacking a woman and child, and committing suicide when police approached.
Four people were wounded in a drive-by shooting in the Natomas area. Those wounded had gathered at a home there.
A man was killed and three others wounded in the early morning.
A shooting at a casino in Kaw Nation territory wounded four.
Four people were shot in a drive-by shooting.

Fifth Third Center Shooting: A gunman entered a loading dock at the Fifth Third Center skyscraper and opened fire before entering the lobby of a building. Four people, including the shooter, were killed and two were injured.
Five people were wounded after an argument escalated outside of a house party, shortly after midnight.
Two people were killed and two wounded at a family birthday party.
An unknown shooter opened fire through an apartment window, and wounded five people.
One man was killed and two others and a woman were injured in an early morning shooting.
Eight people were wounded during a shooting at a dice game at an apartment complex.
Four people were wounded in an early morning shooting at a strip club. The shooter pulled up outside the club and opened fire.
Six people were wounded in the early morning at a large community event.
Five people were injured in a shooting incident during the evening.
A man killed his 11-year-old daughter and wounded her mother and the mother's boyfriend before committing suicide.
Eight people were shot at a nightclub. Police arrived and found a woman with a gunshot wound to the head at the back of the bar. She later died at a hospital.
Seven people were wounded at a party held in a hotel room at the University of Maryland.
Shortly after midnight a man opened fire at a local bar, wounding four.
Three people were shot in the Chicago Loop as they sat at a red light at an intersection by two people. Another person was shot by a stray bullet as they crossed the street.
Three teenagers and an adult male were injured while sitting on a porch.
An unidentified individual fired from a vehicle on a group of people standing outside a home, killing one and injuring three.
Four people were shot in a neighborhood, at a believed house party after a dispute escalated. The wounded are believed to be teenagers.
A man was killed and three wounded in a drive-by shooting in East Oakland.
An argument among a group of people led to someone opening fire, wounding six.
2019 Río Piedras shooting: Six people were killed in a shootout at a housing project.

Jacksonville Landing Shooting: A gunman killed two people and wounded eleven more at a Madden NFL 19 competition before killing himself. The shooter was identified as David Katz, an individual who had reportedly been eliminated from the competition before the shooting.
Two groups of men got into a dispute inside a cigar and hookah lounge and the argument escalated. One man was killed and three injured.
Four people were wounded in an evening shooting a block away from a middle school.
Five people were shot, one fatally, on a street in the early morning.
A woman killed her two children and her husband before attempting to commit suicide.

One person was killed and three others were wounded inside a residence. Authorities took a man into custody in connection with the shooting. According to reports, the deceased victim was shot in the chest.
A man was killed and two adults and a sixteen-year-old were injured after a man entered a home in Morgan Park and opened fire. Police believe the shooting was drug related.
A man killed three women and wounded two in a targeted domestic dispute. One of the wounded was targeted and the others attempted to help her.
Officers responding to shots fired engaged an active shooter and shot the attacker. Eleven people were shot before police stopped the shooter.
One woman and three men were wounded outside a bar.
Two gunmen reportedly shot five people outside a residence. One victim was shot in the chest and later died at Vanderbilt University Medical Center.
A patrol officer discovered four people wounded after an argument escalated late at night. One of the victims has a concealed weapons permit, but officers are unsure who actually fired.
A woman shot and wounded four in a bowling alley after a fight escalated.
A party being held at a park ended in gunfire, with four people being shot. One person succumbed to their injuries.
A 14-year-old boy and five men were wounded while standing on the street.
Five people were shot and wounded during an armed robbery of Liquid Café. One other individual had an unspecified injury "by other means" than gunfire.
One individual was killed and three others wounded after a heated argument escalated.
After an online dispute, a person shot four people in Downtown Orlando.
A shooting by multiple people at a festival wounded five. One of the shooters was fatally shot by a responding officer.
Four people were killed and three injured at a social club.
Four people were injured during a shooting in the Oxford Circle neighborhood of Philadelphia.
Officers responded to a report of multiple shots fired and found four individuals wounded in a home.
Four people were wounded in an evening drive-by on the West Side.
A fight in the Rosedale Heights neighborhood led to a shooting that killed one, and injured four others.
Four men were wounded after a brawl near a gas station.
A rapper's tour van "came under fire" on I-64 after a concert at around 11:05 PM. Four people were injured. It's not clear if the rapper himself was shot.
An eighteen-year-old was killed and three other teens were wounded in a house during the evening.
Four people were shot just after midnight on Halloween.
Four teenagers were shot, two fatally, in a drive by shooting.
A man was killed and three others injured.

Six people were wounded by gunfire in a shooting outside of an apartment complex, following a large fight in the same location the previous day. One of the wounded men was arrested, but charges against him were later dropped.
A fight broke out at an early morning house party and escalated. Two men were killed and three others wounded.
Four people were shot, two fatally.
Two people were killed, and three others were injured, after a fight between two biker gangs led to a gunfight in a bar parking lot in the Fountain City neighborhood.
Four people were killed and one injured after a neighbor entered their apartment and opened fire. The fifth victim died of her injuries later in hospital.
Five people were injured in a shooting at a bar. One of the victims later died of his injuries.

A dispute potentially near I-35 escalated and four people within a car were shot. The car crashed a short time later. Three adults and a thirteen-year-old were wounded and three additional children were not injured.
A woman was shot and killed and nine injured at a large Halloween party of hundred people.
A shootout at a bar between two groups of people wounded six people in the 11th Ward neighborhood.
One person was killed and five injured after an argument escalated in a local bar.
A fight over drugs resulted in one person being killed and three others being wounded.
Four men were shot in the early morning. Two men were later arrested for the shooting and a wounded man died later at the hospital.
Two cousins working as security were shot and killed. Two others were wounded.
A shooting at a party injured four.
Five men were wounded after a driver was angered over a game of dice.
Five were wounded in a shooting after a softball game in the Grand Crossing neighborhood of Chicago.
A gunman walked into a family's front yard and opened fire on a family gathering shortly before midnight. The family had gathered for a funeral and two were killed and eight wounded.
An 18-year-old was arrested after killing a man and wounding three others in a drive-by shooting.
A woman was killed, and three other people were injured, including a teenager, in a revenge shooting.
A man was killed while another man and two children, ages 10 and 14, were wounded.
One person was killed and three others were wounded in a drive-by shooting at a family gathering.
Shortly before midnight someone opened fire in a Miami neighborhood. A man was killed and two adults and an infant girl were wounded.
Two people were killed and several wounded after two men opened fire on a Halloween party.
An argument between two men escalated into a shooting that killed a young girl, and another man. Three children, including a toddler, were also shot.
Two people were killed and two wounded at a mobile home.

Four people were wounded by gunfire following an event where school supplies were distributed to children. A fifth person, a child, received minor injuries after being struck by a dirt bike operated by one of the attackers.
Officers responded to a gunfire locator alert and multiple 911 calls and found two individuals wounded. An additional two transported themselves to the hospital.
One person was killed and three wounded after a shooting at a house party. The party occurred at the home of a Gilroy councilwoman.
Four people, including a teenager, were wounded in a drive-by shooting in the West Garfield Park neighborhood.
A man was killed and three other individuals, including a 15-year-old boy, were injured.
Four people were injured during gunfire during a drive-by shooting following a fight in a Bronx lounge.
Three men and a woman were wounded in a shooting shortly after midnight.
A man was killed and several people wounded after a shooting at a Halloween party.

A man fatally shot three people, including the owner, at a motel in Biloxi before fleeing westward to Gulfport. In Gulfport, he fatally shot another man and carjacked his vehicle, before barricading himself inside a convenience store. The shooter assaulted two employees of the convenience store, but they escaped unharmed, after which he barricaded himself inside an office. The shooter set a fire in the room which caused him to die of smoke inhalation.
A family of five, two adults and three children, were found shot to death in their home in an apparent murder-suicide.
Seven people were wounded in a shooting in the Englewood neighborhood of Chicago.
A vehicle with six passengers – two adults and four juveniles –  was traveling on I-10 when a car next to them opened fire. Five people in the car were wounded.
Four people were wounded in a residential area in the early morning.
Four people were shot during an argument in the Maryvale Village neighborhood.
An argument escalated during a large gathering outside a home, and four people were wounded.
Five people were injured when they were shot during a backyard gathering to mourn the death of a family member who had died in a car accident earlier that month.
A man was killed and five other people were wounded in a drive-by shooting in Prospect Lefferts Gardens in Brooklyn.
Four people were wounded at a large house party in the early morning.
During the filming of a music video at a barber shop, at least one person opened fire from a passing vehicle, wounding four. A fifth person was injured while trying to flee.
Four people were killed and another five people wounded in a shooting at a bar.
After a dispute at a grocery store checkout line, a man pulled a handgun from his sister's waistband and wounded five people. The suspect was arrested.
A gunman ambushed four people waiting in a car at a McDonald's drive through. One person in the car was killed and two adults and a thirteen-year-old were injured.
A man was killed and four others wounded at an outdoor boxing match at the Skyway Plaza.
Three teenagers were fatally shot on a road in northwest Rock Hill. Another person was shot but survived.
An argument inside of an American Legion bar escalated, and five men were shot as they left the bar.
A father killed three of his children and wounded the fourth before killing himself.
An argument at a local open-mike night for rappers at a club escalated when at least two people opened fire. Three men were killed and one injured.
Two people were killed and five injured at a Halloween party that was held at a local banquet hall.
A shooting at a gathering at a Shell gas station wounded three people, and killed one.
Two adults and two children were discovered dead in a home.
A woman shot and injured four people in a street fight in the East Liberty neighborhood of Pittsburgh. She later turned herself in to police.
Five people were wounded in a drive-by-shooting while standing outside a house during a party. A seventeen-year-old and four adults were among the injured.
Four people were shot at a party inside an event center.
A fight at a house party led to six people being shot, with two dying from their injuries.
Three people were wounded and a fourth later died at the hospital in a shooting.
Two adults and two children were wounded in a shooting at a party at a park in north Columbus.
A man was killed and three others wounded after gunfire erupted in front of a convenience store.
Three people were wounded at a birthday party and two more were wounded as the tour bus transporting some of the wounded was later shot at.
Four people were shot, one fatally, during the early morning hours.
A man was killed and three others wounded.
One person was killed and four others were shot in an early-morning shooting in the Crocker-Amazon neighborhood of San Francisco.
An argument at an early morning house party escalated and one man was killed. Another adult and two seventeen-year-old girls were wounded.
Four people were wounded after an argument in an alley escalated.
Five people were shot, one fatally, in a shooting at a bar in the Muscupiabe neighborhood.
Four men were wounded after two cars drove by a crowd of people and opened fire.
After being kicked out of a sports bar following several fights, a man returned with a gun and killed a bartender. Three others were wounded by gunfire. The shooter was taken into custody.
A gunman walked into an East Garfield Park home and opened fire. He killed one man and wounded four others.
A man was killed and three wounded in a suspected robbery shortly before midnight.
Five people were shot in the Hotel District neighborhood during the late night hours.
Four people were wounded after an individual fired a shotgun towards a group of people at a house party.
A man wounded four people at a gas station after shooting at them from his truck. He was arrested by police.
Two men were discovered wounded at a home near Belmont University, and two others arrived at local hospitals later.

Two people, including a security guard, were shot and killed at a mall, and four others were wounded. The shooter was injured by responding officers and died the next day after being taken into custody.
Four people were shot, two fatally, in a drive-by shooting in the West Englewood neighborhood.
Four people were injured while attending a large party after an individual fired into the air.
Four people were wounded by a gunman who was later taken into custody.
Shortly after midnight two men approached a home hosting a Halloween themed house party opened fire on the closed garage door. A 21-year-old college student was killed and five others were wounded.
Three teenagers and an adult were wounded after a shooting near an elementary school.
A fight at a sports bar led to a shooting that injured four during the early morning hours in the Goldest East neighborhood.
Four young women were injured after an individual fired into a home were a house party was being held.
Four people were wounded by a gunman.
A patrol officer heard gunfire near a local lounge in the early morning, and found a wounded man. Four others were transported by private vehicles to local hospitals.
Two people were killed, and two others injured at an off-roading event.
Four people were injured in a shooting during the night in central Petersburg.
A man was killed and three injured after unknown individuals attempted to crash a house party and began shooting.
Two people were killed and four were injured in a drive-by shooting in North Philadelphia.
Shortly before midnight two men were killed and four injured at a local restaurant.
Two people were killed and three injured in a shooting on Jones Street.

A 23-year old man shot at random people at Edmund Burke School from his apartment with a sniper-style set-up, wounding four—including a child, in the Forest Hills neighborhood. The man committed suicide as officers entered his apartment.
Four men were shot and killed at an apartment complex after a disturbance between roommates escalated.
One person was killed and four were injured in the Austin neighborhood of Chicago.
Three people were killed and one wounded after an argument occurred in the early morning at a private motorcycle club over a motorcycle. The wounded victim is refusing to cooperate with police.
Six people were wounded in an early morning shooting at a local bar.
Four people were injured in the Walnut Hills neighborhood.
A man killed his mother then drove to a gas station where he attempted to kidnap a clerk then killed a man and injured the clerk before robbing another gas station and committing suicide.
Four people were wounded at Humboldt Park when they were shot at by two people in a car.
Six people were injured in a drive-by shooting and one was killed. Three of the injured were children and three were adults. The victim killed was one year old.
A teenager was killed and one adult and three juveniles wounded at a Halloween party.
A man shot to death his parents and another couple a quarter-mile apart from each other inside their homes.
A 17-year-old boy was killed and three adults were injured in the Lower West Side.
Four people were wounded by gunfire at a house party.
A man was killed and another and two women were injured in an evening shooting.
A man was killed and seven others wounded at an off-campus party about two blocks from Fort Valley State University.
A man shot four of his family members, including two children, as they slept before shooting himself.
Two men were killed and a woman and man injured in an early morning shooting.
Eight people were wounded when a group of men approached them in a courtyard and began shooting.
Seven people were wounded in an evening shooting in Southwest Baltimore. Two people were discovered at the scene and five were later discovered at area hospitals.
Five people were wounded outside a Chatham liqueur store when a man opened fire and then fled.
A man shot his girlfriend and their two young children before shooting himself.
Five people were wounded at The SPOTT Lifestyle and Swingers Club.
Two shooters killed one person and wounded five others when they began shooting at a group standing on a sidewalk.
A party after a University of Louisiana football game in Moore Park led to an early morning shooting after an argument escalated. Two people were wounded and two killed.
Four people were wounded in the parking lot of a banquet hall that was hosting a Halloween party.
A fight at an Easter party being held at a home ended in gunshots, with a man being killed and three others, including two juveniles, being injured.
Four people were wounded after shot were fired into their car.
Six people were shot when a man pulled a handgun from his waistband during a fight. The suspect was taken into custody.
Four men were injured at a gas station in an evening shooting in Southwest Philadelphia.
Five adults and two teenagers were wounded in a drive-by shooting.
Five people were shot during the late evening hours.
Three adults and three juveniles were injured after a fight escalated.
Six people were injured during a shooting at a house party.
A man was killed and four others were injured at a local grocery store early in the morning. One of the injured died three days later.
Three adults were killed and a fourth later died at the hospital in a night time shooting.
One teenage boy died, and three others are in a hospital, after a shooting in the Centennial neighborhood.
Ten people were shot, two fatally, during a bar fight that escalated.
One person was killed and three were injured in the Austin neighborhood of Chicago.
Four people were wounded in an evening shooting at a downtown hotel. Additional guns and pills were discovered at the scene of the shooting.
A gunman exited a subway station and shot four people in the Flatbush section of Brooklyn.
Four people were shot in the Fairhill neighborhood.
A man was killed and three women injured in an early morning shooting.
Four people were injured when a gunman began shooting from a car at a group of people who were grilling and playing basketball in a park.
Four people were inside a vehicle when they were hit by gunfire near the West Garfield Park on the West Side. A man died and two adults and a seventeen-year-old girl were wounded.
A woman shot and killed her father, sister and two workers at their home in the afternoon.
A shooting at an Easter party being hosted at a nightclub wounded nine.
Six people were shot, one fatally, at an intersection in the Mid-City Area.

After becoming upset at a party, a man killed one person and wounded three others, including his girlfriend. He was driven from the scene by his friend and his friend's wife. He later shot and killed his friend, but his attempt to kill his friend's wife failed when his gun malfunctioned.

A man opened fire after he was ejected from a nightclub by firing into the club while standing in the road. Three people were discovered in the club and five were taken to the hospital in private vehicles.
A man killed his roommate's teenage daughter and her boyfriend, and wounded his roommate and her 14-year-old son. He later killed himself.
A shooting in the Parkway neighborhood wounded three, and killed one, during the early morning hours.
A man was killed, and four others and a woman injured, in a possible drive-by in the Columbia Heights District.
Four people were injured when shots were fired during a dispute in a parking lot.
A woman and her six-year-old daughter were killed and her other daughters aged sixteen and ten-years-old were wounded. The woman's boyfriend was arrested as a person of interest.
Responding officers found an SUV in a ditch with bullet holes and blood near Winzer Park. Four adults and a juvenile were later identified at local hospitals although none had reached out to police.

2022 Pittsburgh shooting: An early morning shooting at a party held at an Airbnb rental property in the East Allegheny neighborhood killed two juveniles, and wounded nine others. Five people sustained injuries such as broken bones and cuts when they jumped out windows to escape the gunfire.
Three men were killed and one injured after an argument about cigarettes escalated outside a West Garfield Park convenience store.
Four people were injured in a drive-by shooting.
At least two gunmen opened fire on a group of people in the city's Frankford neighborhood. One man was killed and six others wounded.
A 19-year-old was killed and three teenagers were wounded in the early morning in the Baden neighborhood.
Four people were shot, including two children, during a house party.
A man and woman were killed, and two other women injured, in the Wilmington neighborhood after an individual shot into a crowd of people.
Four people were injured in a shooting.
A man was killed and one man and three women were injured in an early morning shooting at a house party. Two teenagers were arrested and charged for the shooting.
Responding officers found four people wounded and shell casings around a car in the intersection.
An exchange of gunfire behind a bar left four wounded.
Two adults killed, two juveniles injured in east Cheyenne shooting.
One person was killed and four were injured in a shooting following a verbal altercation at an inn.
One man was killed and three injured in an evening shooting at a Brooklyn building. Neighbors claim that the building was a local gambling den.
Five people were wounded outside a local bar after an unknown number of people opened fire.
Seven people were shot, one fatally, during a shooting at a pasture party and trail ride.
Four individuals were wounded after an individual opened fire.
Four people were injured when they were shot after a fight broke out.
Two men and two women were shot in an evening shooting, with one victim in critical condition.
A person was killed and seven others wounded at Grambling State University during a homecoming event in the early morning.
A shooting killed one, and injured three others, in northwest Baltimore during the evening.
Responding police officers discovered a car covered in gunshots, and discovered a deceased male and two men and a female injured. One of the injured men later died.
Two gunmen killed three people and injured seven others in a shooting at a daiquiri shop.
Police responding to reports of an early morning shooting found three men dead outside an establishment. Four additional wounded were identified at the hospital after transporting themselves.
Six people were wounded at a one-year anniversary vigil for a man killed in the location. Neighbors refused to cooperate with police due to fear of retaliation.
Columbiana Centre shooting: Nine people were shot, and five others were injured while fleeing a shooting at the Columbiana Centre, after at least one person opened fire.
An argument escalated between two men outside a Laurel District bar, leading to a man killed and three men and a woman injured.
Two people were killed and six were injured in a drive-by shooting by a liquor store.

A fight broke out between two women inside a store and shortly after three men arrived with guns and entered the store. The men opened fire, and customers returned fire, with one man killed and three adults and two juveniles injured.
Gunfire erupted at a party hall wounding eleven and killing one, responding police opened fire on a man holding a gun and wounded him.
An argument between two men at a bar escalated, with them opening fire on each other and wounding one another. Two bystanders were also shot.
A feud between two men led to four people being injured after it escalated in the North Fairmont neighborhood.
Three children and an adult were injured in a shooting.
A nine-year-old girl was killed and two adults and a six-year-old girl were wounded at a Del Paso Heights park. They were part of a family gathering when a gunman drove up and opened fire.
Three people were killed and three injured after a man opened fire inside a night club.
Shortly after midnight, five people were shot, one fatally, in the Armory Square neighborhood.
One person was killed and three others injured at a local apartment complex.
A man killed his father and stepmother, as well as their adopted son and his stepmother's son, before killing himself in a murder–suicide at a nursing home.
At least five people were wounded in an early morning shooting at a house party. An argument had broken out and escalated into gun fire.
Four people were wounded in the parking lot of a club in the early morning. One of the wounded died two days later.
A group of people approached another group and opened fire, killing two and wounding two others in the Pacific neighborhood.
Two adults, a 16-year-old girl, and a 17-year-old boy were killed and two others injured in a mobile home park.
One person was killed and six were injured in a shootout involving multiple gunmen at a bar after the filming of a rap music video.
A seventeen-year-old girl and three others were wounded in an evening shooting in Rainier Valley.
Five people were wounded at a high school football game.

Police officers responding to reports of a suspicious vehicle found a woman inside a Jeep, who refused to cooperate with officers. She then pulled out a gun when officers attempted to remove her from the vehicle and opened fire, wounding three officers before being fatally shot.
Three young adult males and a 17-year-old boy were injured in the back of a house in the West Town neighborhood.
A gunman shot at a moving car, killing two occupants and injuring the other two.
Four people were wounded in a shooting in the Central Business District. Victims ran away from the original scene causing officers to believe there were more shootings than actual.
Responding police found five people wounded in Ventura Village. One of the wounded later died at the hospital.
Four people were shot, one fatally, in the Allerton neighborhood of The Bronx.
A woman shot and killed one woman and injured three others after a continuation of an argument escalated.
Six people were injured in a drive-by shooting.
Two women and three men were wounded in a shooting shortly before midnight in a rental hall.
A man was killed and three others wounded after two shooters opened fire on a Naples Park home. The shooters were also wounded.

2022 New York City Subway attack: Ten people were shot when a gunman motivated by black supremacy opened fire on a New York City Subway train as it approached the 36th Street station in the Sunset Park neighborhood. Immediately before the attack, the assailant donned a gas mask and threw smoke bombs. The incident caused 19 others to be injured as they fled. The suspect was arrested the next day.
Two men were killed and three other individuals injured at a local convenience store, in the early morning.
Four people were injured when a truck pulled up beside a car and one or more of its occupants began shooting. A suspect was arrested.
Four North Carolina A&T State University students were wounded in an off-campus apartment complex.
Three adults were killed in a home and an infant was found wounded.
First responders found two men dead, and four others injured, after a shooting.
A husband, wife and their five-year-old son were killed while the grandmother was injured in a targeted attack.
Five people were wounded when someone began firing at them while they stood on a sidewalk.
Seven people were shot at a funeral home.
Three wounded were found by responding officers, a fourth flagged down officers and two others were found at local hospitals.
A targeted shooting at a nightclub wounded ten, and killed two, after two men opened fire in the Oakhill Jackson neighborhood.
A man and a seven-year-old girl were killed, and another man and a 11-year-old boy were injured after an argument apparently escalated.
Four people were wounded in a shooting.
Two men and two women were wounded inside an apartment with no signs of a break-in.
Two people were killed and three injured in a shooting near a nightclub.
Police found three people shot at two related shootings, after a  victim flagged down a police cruiser.
Three adults and a child were wounded in a shooting.
Two people were killed and five injured when they were shot by four gunmen in a park.
Five men were wounded shortly before midnight while standing on a porch in the Logan section of the city.
One person was killed and 14 injured in a shootout at a bar.
A fight at a birthday party being held at an event venue erupted into gunfire, with five people being injured, and another person being killed, both in and outside the building.
A 14-year-old boy shot dead five family members – two adults and three children – in an Alabama residence. He confessed the crime to the police.
One person was killed and four were injured after a shooter opened fire into a backyard party.
Two men were killed and two wounded in an afternoon shooting. The men were recording a music video and got into an argument with another group which escalated.
Four bystanders were wounded at an after hours club  in an early morning targeted shooting.
An early morning shooting at a gathering being held at an apartment complex killed one, and injured five.
Four men were wounded in a drive-by shooting outside of a CTA Green Line station in Washington Park.
Four people were wounded when three gunmen began shooting at them at a restaurant.
Four men and two women were injured in an early morning shooting after a large crowd had congregated outside a Gentleman's club in the city's southwest side.
A man was killed and four others injured in an early morning drive-by outside a Wicker Park nightclub.
A shooting carried out by two men across multiple blocks wounded four, including two teenagers.
Two men were killed and a woman and small child injured during a home invasion.
Four people were wounded when shots were fired during a large fight in an apartment complex. Four people were arrested on other charges, but the shooter or shooters were not identified.
Four people were wounded near an intersection in the afternoon after an argument escalated. The gunman walked away to his vehicle, retrieved a pistol, opened fire, and drove away.
A man was killed and four others wounded after a drive-by shooting at a house party in the early morning.

A fight inside a bar in the Wingate neighborhood spilled outside, where multiple men pulled out firearms and opened fire at each other, resulting in the death of one man, and injuries to three others.
Four people were shot at a private party at a Moose Lodge.
Two people were killed and four others were injured when a gunman began shooting at them while they were standing in a yard.
A man shot and wounded four people shortly before midnight, with one victim discovered in a vehicle by police.
Three 18-year-olds and a 16-year-old were wounded in South Dallas.
Four people were shot outside a convenience store in the Model City neighborhood during the early morning.
Six adult males and a 15-year-old boy were wounded outside a kindergarten after an argument over a Lanett vs. Lafayette football game escalated.
Two gunmen killed one person and injured four others.
A nineteen-year-old was killed and three others injured in an evening shooting.
Responding officers found one man deceased and six wounded were later found in local hospitals.
A man fatally shot his estranged wife, a relative, and another person in a home before shooting himself.
Three men and a 17-year-old boy were wounded in a shooting.
Masked men drove up in a car and began shooting into a crowd, killing a ten-year-old girl and injuring three others. Three people were arrested in relation to the shooting.

Two teens, aged fifteen and sixteen-years-old and two adults were wounded just before midnight at a block party in West Philadelphia. The teens and one adult had been leaving the party when the gunman opened fire.
Responding officers found one man killed and three wounded.

A man shot two women in the Frankford neighborhood before being pursued by police to an apartment building, where he barricaded himself inside and engaged in a gunfight with police. The man wounded a SEPTA police officer before fatally shooting himself.
Four people were found shot in the early morning.
Four people were wounded during a shooting following a fight at a party.
One man died and three others injured after someone opened fire on an early morning party in an apartment complex parking lot.
Two people were killed and three others wounded after a man went on a multi-parish shooting spree. He was later arrested with a self-inflicted gunshot wound and a dog bite.
Four people were shot, one of them fatally, in the Clay Arsenal neighborhood.
Midland–Odessa shooting: Eight people were killed, including the perpetrator, and 25 were wounded when a gunman opened fire on police and civilians after fleeing from a traffic stop.
