Five people were injured when a shooter fired into a group of people gathered in a parking lot outside a club.

Two people were killed and six injured in a shooting at a motorcycle club where over 100 people had gathered. Four others suffered injuries from broken glass and debris while fleeing from the gunfire.
Four men were wounded in Southeast Baltimore in the afternoon.
A large fight involving multiple juveniles erupted into gunfire. A shooter wounded three juveniles, and an adult man.
A man was killed and three others were injured at a University of North Carolina at Charlotte off-campus apartment complex.
Four people were injured in a shooting.
Two men and two women were injured in an early morning drive-by shooting in Marquette Park on the Southwest Side.
Responding police discovered a deceased man and another wounded, with two more identified at local hospitals.
Four people were shot, two fatally, near a playground in the Crocker-Amazon neighborhood.
Four people were injured after an argument escalated.
One person was killed and three people were wounded in a shooting outside a nightclub in Scott's Addition.
Four teenagers aged between seventeen and nineteen-years-old were injured in a late night shooting in the Frankford section of the city.
Three adults were killed and another wounded after two men came back thirty minutes after an argument over parking and opened fire.

2022 Sacramento shooting: A shootout between the Crips and Bloods, and the Bloods' local ally the G-Mobb gang, ended with one member of each gang being killed, and one Crips member being injured. Three bystanders were killed, while another eleven were wounded.
Ten people, ranging in age from 15 to 18, were injured at a high school football game after a fight escalated.
Five people were wounded in a shooting near a community center. Police believe the shooting was spurred by an earlier fight over a dice game.
A woman was killed and her mother and young child were injured when a man entered the home and shot. He shot and injured an additional woman while carjacking her in an attempt to flee.
Two teenagers and two adults were wounded in the early morning after someone opened fire on another car on the Near North Side.

A man opened fire inside a home in Parkin, killing one and wounding another. Responding police spotted him as he drove west away from the scene, leading to a chase that ended in Wynne, where he engaged in a gunfight, wounding a police officer before being fatally shot.
A woman was killed and three others were injured in a possible retaliation to a previous stabbing.
Four people were injured in a drive-by shooting while they were inside their car at restaurant.
Three men and two women were injured outside a bar early in the morning after an argument escalated. The bar was the scene of another mass shooting in June were a man died and six were injured.
Five people were wounded when a police officer opened fire on an armed suspect who returned fire before he fled the area.
Four people were shot as they left a party in the Willert Park neighborhood in the early morning.
A 16-year-old boy was killed, while two teen boys – a 14-year-old and 15-year-old – and an adult woman were injured.
Gunmen injured four people—two inside a mobile home, and two in separate vehicles outside of the home.

A man barged into a home in the early morning and opened fire, wounding four adults and killing a four-year-old child. The child reportedly was held by his mother when the man opened fire and was struck and killed in her arms.
A woman was killed and five people were wounded in East Baltimore.

During a concert just after midnight, a person fired a shot into the air, and immediately afterward, another person opened fire into the crowd of concertgoers. Sixteen people were shot, including three teenagers, and one person died.
A man killed his wife, mother-in-law, and one of his three-year-old twin daughters before committing suicide.
A man killed his wife and three children in their home before killing himself in a murder–suicide.
Two women were discovered wounded in front of a house in Queens by police. Two men arrived at the hospital by private vehicles at a later time.
Four adults were wounded at a music studio shortly before midnight.
Five people were shot in two related shootings in the same neighborhood. Four people were shot in the first shooting, and a fifth was shot in the other.
A 17-year-old boy was killed and three adults were wounded after a large group was fired upon.
Following a fight, a man was killed and four other people were injured by gunshots. Two people were arrested.
A woman was killed and three others injured in a housing complex parking lot shortly after midnight. A large crowd had gathered and someone opened fire.
A man was killed and three others wounded after four people exited a vehicle and opened fire on them. The victims were doing work in a parking lot behind a church.
Five people were shot, one fatally, in the parking lot of a bar in the early morning.
Police responded to a party due to a shots fired call and found three dead and four wounded.
Six people, including a suspect, were wounded during a shooting at a bar.
A woman was killed and four other people were injured in an early morning shooting at a street party.
Responding police found four injured due to an evening shooting and one later died at the hospital.
Four people were shot in an early morning shooting outside a bar. One person was found dead by responding police.
A man was killed and three were injured while attending a basketball tournament.
Four people were injured in a shooting.
Rochester shooting: Two people were killed and 14 others were injured in Rochester at a backyard party on Pennsylvania Avenue.
A teen shot four people inside a vehicle at an intersection.
Four people were shot behind a bar, one fatally, just after midnight.
Two people were killed and three were injured, including a police officer, in a shooting. A suspect was apprehended.
A man killed his wife and one of his children and wounded his other two children before setting the house on fire and killing himself in a murder–suicide.

Four people were wounded in West Pullman less than an hour after the shooting in West Englewood. Two sedans pulled up to a group outside and opened fire towards people on the sidewalk, home porch and inside the home.
Three men and a juvenile were wounded at a local gas station.
An argument led to a gunfight that injured five near midnight.
Seven people were wounded at a two-year-old's birthday party after a fight escalated.
Four people were injured in Brooklyn when they were shot at while standing outside.
Four men were wounded in West Englewood while standing outside when someone opened fire.
A man was killed and four others wounded in an early morning drive by shooting at a Waffle House.
Police officers responding to a home robbery were fired upon by the suspect, who wounded two, and killed one. Officers returned fire and killed the suspect.
An eight-year-old girl was killed and three others were wounded in a shooting near Soldan High School.
Four people were injured in a shooting.
Police officers responded to a shooting after a ShotShopper alert and found four people wounded.
A man was killed and two adults and a teenager were wounded at an early morning hotel party,
A motorist fleeing a traffic stop opened fire as he was being pursued by police, wounding three officers, before being shot by an officer at the end of a car chase.
Two men were killed and a man and woman were injured in a drive-by shooting.
Three people were killed and three others were wounded during a Fourth of July party. Police believe the shooting was gang-related.
Five people were shot in an evening shooting.
A man was killed and two adults and a teenager wounded at an apartment complex.
A shooting during an illegal street-racing event in the St. Johns neighborhood wounded four, including two teenagers, and one child. The suspect, an adult male, was also injured.
A man opened fire on patrons at a bar, killing two and wounding two others, after being kicked out.
Six people were injured while walking down the street. A suspect was taken into custody.
Four people were wounded in a drive-by afternoon shooting, near I-630.
Five adults were wounded and one killed in Southwest D.C. late at night.
A shooting at an intersection in the Little Woods neighborhood killed two, and injured two others.
Four people, including a social worker and a security guard were wounded in the Skid Row district.
One person was killed and five were injured in a shooting at a Fourth of July party.

Two men were killed and three wounded while playing basketball at the Roberto Clemente Playground in Spring Garden. Police believe the men were targeted as the three shooters chased them down, after the first confrontation.
Five adults and a teenager were wounded after an argument at a hotel birthday party celebration escalated.
A drive-by shooting in northern Hollister killed two, and injured three.
Four female students from Clark Atlanta University and Spelman College were wounded during a block party.
One person was killed and three were wounded.
Two people were killed and three others injured in a quintuple shooting near San Jose State University.
Five bystanders were wounded when passengers of two separate cars opened fire on one another while driving down a Fulton River District road.
A shooting at a downtown nightclub during the early morning hours wounded four.
Four teenagers were wounded after an argument escalated during a gathering in a hotel room.
After a bar fight spilled into a parking lot, shots were fired, killing one person and wounding three others.
Five people, including three teenagers, were wounded in a drive by shooting. The group were outside celebrating Mexican Independence.
A woman was killed and three others injured in the early morning after a man opened fire on a car in Park Manor.

An argument between two groups of people outside a bar in Northwest Virginia Beach just after midnight led to a shooting that injured four. Officers nearby responded and fired at one of the shooters, but they escaped uninjured.
Seven people were injured in a shooting at a party.
One person was killed and five others were wounded in a drive-by shooting.
Three people were wounded in a vehicle and a fourth while walking down the street, after a drug deal turned into a robbery. One of the wounded was an eight-year-old girl.
A man was fatally shot and three others injured in a gunfire incident on Bloomington Avenue in the Phillips neighborhood.
A fight outside The Citadel mall during the late evening escalated into a shooting that killed two, and wounded two others.
Police responded to a shooting call and discovered four people wounded.
Four people were injured in a shooting.
Two people died and six others were injured in an overnight shooting near Rutgers University.
A man was killed and two adults and a teenager wounded in Humboldt Park on the Northwest Side.
An argument between two groups of people at a Tanger Outlets mall led to a shooting that injured five, including a child and two teenagers.
A woman was killed, and responding officers engaged with the suspect causing an officer, bystander and the suspect to be wounded.

A woman and a 17-month-old child were killed in a shooting that injured two others. One person was taken into custody, although police suspect others were involved. Police believe the shooting was gang-related.
Seven people were wounded in a late night shooting outside a business in the city's southeast side. One victim's injuries were considered life-threatening.
A man opened fire outside a club in Inwood in Upper Manhattan wounding four. Responding officers opened fire an wounded him.
An attempted burglary at a home led to a gunfight, with two residents being injured, and two robbers being injured.
Four men and a teenage boy were wounded.
Six people were injured when a gunman opened fire on three people on a sidewalk. In addition to the three people on the sidewalk, three children in a car were wounded.

A man opened fire inside a vehicle on I-24 and killed one person in his vehicle and wounded another. He attempted to carjack three vehicles and wounded two people, before taking two hostages. At the end of the hostage taking a hostage and the gunman were dead and the other hostage released.

Two groups of people began fighting in a bar and others joined in as it spilled into the parking lot. Some fighters got into cars and opened fire while driving away killing three and wounding three others.
Four men, including a teenager, were shot in a parking lot just after midnight in the Valley Oak neighborhood. The teenager died as he was frantically driven to a hospital by a family member.
Two people were killed and three wounded in a shooting near Alabama State University.
Several shooters fired into a crowd that was fleeing a nightclub, killing one person and injuring six. Police arrested one suspect, and believe the shooting was gang-related.
A security guard and three club goers were wounded after an individual opened fire from a car shortly after midnight.
Six adults were wounded in East Garfield Park on the West Side in the early morning.
Four men were shot by someone who approached them and opened fire as they stood on the sidewalk in the South Shore neighborhood. Two of the victims later died from their injuries.
A man killed his girlfriend and injured five others and a dog before being wounded by police and arrested.
Six people were injured at a barbecue when an unknown person walked into the yard and began firing.
A man was killed and two adults and a seventeen-year-old boy were wounded while sitting on a homes porch in Englewood, after two men exited a vehicle and opened fire.
Four people including a teenager were wounded in East Oakland.
Four people were shot outside of a bar after an altercation.
Six Philadelphia Police officers were shot during an eight-hour standoff while attempting to serve a drug warrant.
Five people were injured when several people began exchanging gunfire. One suspect was arrested.

A man opened fire at an early morning house party after an argument escalated in the Austin neighborhood. Another individual returned fire causing the first shooter and three others to be wounded and two others killed.
Four men were wounded in the early morning.
Crossfire between two gunmen injured 10 victims from a crowd of 1,000 spring break celebration attendees at the 'Space Dallas' party hall.
Police responded to calls of shots fired and found a deceased male and three women wounded. One died at the hospital from their injuries.
Capital Gazette shooting: A gunman entered the offices of The Capital Gazette and killed five employees and wounded two others.
Four adults and a teenager were wounded after a verbal altercation at a house party escalated.
Responding police found two adults killed and four adults and a child wounded.
An argument at a party led to someone opening fire, wounding four people, in the Franklin Heights neighborhood.
Four people were wounded in a shooting.
One person was killed and three were injured when at least one person began shooting at them outside a mini-mart.
Five people were wounded at a large party, with one aged sixteen-years-old.
Shortly after midnight six people were wounded at a large house party.

Four teenagers were shot outside another teen's birthday party being held at a production studio, with one dying from their injuries. The shooting was sparked by an argument in the parking lot of the studio.
A police officer was killed and two were wounded after a suspect opened fire during a traffic stop. The suspect was killed by police.
During an argument between neighbors, two people drew weapons and wounded four people. One suspect was arrested.
Four minutes after a shooting, police were alerted to a second in which three men died, and one wounded.

Two adults arrived at a home and engaged in an argument with the four adults there over a 10-month old. The dispute escalated and the four adults living at the home were killed and the two suspects kidnapped the child.
Four people were shot at the annual SXSW festival in Downtown Austin.
A man shot and killed his estranged wife and a man, then wounded another man before committing suicide.
Four victims were injured in a drive-by shooting outside a bodega.
A man was killed and three others wounded in the Wellston neighborhood.
A man murdered his parents and sister and wounded another sibling before committing suicide.
Five people were shot, three fatally, in the parking lot of a Baymont Inn in the Terry Sanford neighborhood.
Six people were injured when they were shot by a gunman in a car in Garfield Park.
Six people were injured when a gunman began firing upon them as they stood near a park.
Five people including a seventeen-year-old were injured while playing a dice game when a vehicle pulled up and opened fire.
Four people were wounded at the Rosa Parks Metro Station in Willowbrook.
Ten people were shot during a drive-by shooting outside a party venue in the South Dallas neighborhood.
Four people were injured in an overnight shooting in the parking lot of a McDonald's restaurant.
One person was killed and six were injured during a fight at a birthday party. One of the wounded was arrested.
Four people including a fourteen-year-old boy were injured in Central City.
Collierville Kroger shooting: A worker at a third-party venue inside the store opened fire in a Kroger, killing one and injuring 14, before taking his own life.
A gunfight between two people at a car show killed one bystander, and wounded 26 others, including five children.
Four people were injured in a shooting.
Four people were wounded when an uninvited guest at a birthday party at an event center began shooting.
A fifteen-year-old shooter opened fire at a group of people in a drive-by shooting, including a six-year-old in Brooklyn. Police believe the shooting to be gang related.
Four men were wounded in the Mantua neighborhood.
During the early morning hours, five people were shot. A woman was found dead by responding police.
Four men were injured during a shoot-out at a convenience store.
Four people were injured in a shooting at a block party.
An eighteen-year-old was killed and four others injured after a fight broke out during a party in the Butler-Tarkington neighborhood over a broken table.
Two teenagers were killed and two others injured in a home invasion. Three days earlier a relative of the two deceased had been killed in another home.
Five people were shot, one fatally, during the early morning hours in Downtown Norfolk.
Four people were injured in a drive-by shooting in Marquette Park.
One person was killed and three were injured in a shooting. Six teenage suspects were arrested in relation to the shooting after leading police on a car chase.
A shooting at a large marijuana grow house left seven people dead.
A man opened fire and wounded four adults and one child near Alabama Avenue, Southeast.
Five people, including a baby, were shot in a drive by shooting. The baby and another person were critically injured.
A gunman wearing body armor killed another man and wounded three responding police officers before being arrested.
One person was killed and three were wounded in a shooting.
An eight-year-old girl was killed and three others injured when another vehicle opened fire on them while they were sitting in another car in the Canaryville neighborhood.
A man was killed and four others wounded, with the deceased found behind the wheel of a vehicle.
Four people were shot at a party being hosted at a house in the Far Greater Northside Historical neighborhood, with one dying.
Two people were killed and two were injured in a shooting that also involved a motor vehicle crash.
After several fights inside a bar led the bar owner to close for the night, the fights continued outside before escalating to a shooting in which five people were wounded.
Four people were wounded in the South Shore neighborhood in a drive-by shooting. Three adults and a seventeen-year-old were injured.
A man was killed and five others injured in a drive-by shooting in the Fern Rock neighborhood.
Gunfire erupted at a party being held in a parking lot being held in the Eastside neighborhood. Four people were injured.
A man killed two women and a man, before killing himself in a triple murder–suicide.
Four people were injured in a gang-related shooting.
Four people were wounded at a large house party after a fight broke out in the early morning.
A man was killed and three others wounded while at a vigil for another homicide victim, when a group of people opened fire from a black SUV.

As a Broward County Transit bus traveled westward along Broward Boulevard to the Fort Lauderdale Police Department, a shooter opened fire inside, killing two, and wounding two others. The shooting caused the bus driver to hop the median and drive on the wrong side of the road as she drove frantically towards the police station, striking an SUV and taxi cab along the way, injuring three others. The shooter surrendered to responding police.
Four people were shot and injured after a dispute.
One person was killed and four others were injured after being shot at from a vehicle.
Two people opened fire in an apartment and wounded three adults and a five-year-old child.
After an argument escalated someone opened fire shortly after midnight killing one adult and wounding one adult and seven children.
Four people were shot in a drive-by shooting in the West Garfield Park neighborhood, including a child.
A man killed his uncle, grandmother and mother before he set the house on fire and committed suicide in a triple murder–suicide.
Four people were injured in a shooting.
Responding officers found a wounded man and three other wounded individuals transported themselves to the hospital.

During an argument one of the victims pulled out her gun and pointed it at the ground, after things calmed down she put it away and began to enter a car with her husband, and two children. The man she was arguing with opened fire once they got to the car, wounding her, her husband and two children.
A shooter opened fire on a group of men standing outside a market in northern Irvington during the late-night hours, killing one, and injuring three.
One person was killed and three were wounded after a large fight broke out following a funeral service.
One person was killed and three were injured when their car was shot at from another car.
Six people were wounded in Swope Park where a large crowd had gathered to watch cars do burnouts and donuts.
Two adults were killed and three others and a teenager wounded shortly after midnight when a man opened fire.
As a car idled at an intersection, another car pulled up to it and someone inside opened fire, wounding five people inside.
Four people were injured in a shooting during a candlelight vigil in Crown Heights.
One person was killed and three were wounded in a fight that progressed to a shooting outside of a liquor store.
One woman was killed and three others injured in the Hamilton Heights neighborhood.
A man was killed and three others wounded in the early morning while outside a club.

An attempted negotiation between a man and suspected thieves, who he thought stole a gun and cash from his car three days earlier, escalated into a gun battle after one of the suspects shot the man before the man returned fire and killed the suspect. As an employee of the man tried to render first-aid to the first suspect, a second suspect shot them before being shot themselves.
One man was killed and three others were injured in an early morning shooting.
Four people were wounded in a shooting.
Responding officers found a man dead and two wounded at an early morning birthday party. Four other wounded were identified at the hospital.
Five people were wounded while sitting on a porch in Austin during the early morning, after two men exited a vehicle and opened fire.
A man shot three people, killing one, in the Glenwood Hills neighborhood. Responding police were attacked by the shooter, who injured two officers, before being shot and killed himself.
Four people were discovered wounded in an overnight shooting.
Four people were wounded in a shooting.
Five people were wounded at a night club, and separate charges were filed against the club owner for operating during COVID-19 restrictions.

Two people were killed and two injured after someone shot down an alley at a group standing outside, who were attending a party. The shooting occurred on the anniversary of a similar mass shooting in 2020.
A fight among a large group of teenagers at a park in southwest Reading led to gunfire, wounding three, and killing one. All of the victims were students of Governor Mifflin School District.
One person was killed and seven others were injured in a shooting in the Lawndale community.
Five people were injured when someone drew a gun and began shooting during a fight.
A woman and three men were wounded after a party with multiple motorcycle clubs, had a large fight in the parking lot with multiple shooters.
A man was killed and three others wounded at a BBQ at Claremont Park in the Bronx, after an argument escalated.
A car pulled up to a group of people outside a Little Caesars in South Chicago and someone in the vehicle opened fire, wounding seven people.
Seven people were wounded in a drive-by shooting near Douglass Park.
A man returned after an argument and wounded four people. He was later taken into custody.

A man was found wounded at the River Market district, with witnesses stating the shooter opened fire after pulling a gun from his fanny pack. Three children aged, seventeen, sixteen and twelve-years-old were also wounded.
Two people were killed and two wounded at a liquor store in the early morning.

An early morning shooting during a party being held at an apartment lead to the death of a woman, and injuries to four others, including two teenagers. The apartment complex is located just off the campus of the University of South Carolina, but no students were shot.
2019 Dayton shooting: A gunman killed nine people and injured 27 outside of a bar after he was denied entry, before being killed by police.
Two people were killed and three people were injured in a shooting after a fight at a party.
Two men were discovered wounded by responding officers, one of whom later died at the hospital. Two more wounded were identified after transporting themselves to the hospital.
Four people were shot outside a club in the East Flatbush area of Brooklyn after a dispute.
In the early morning hours at a hookah bar, four people were shot—two fatally, in the Brown Square neighborhood.
2019 El Paso shooting: 23 people were killed and 23 were injured at a Walmart near the Cielo Vista Mall in a Hispanophobic massacre. The perpetrator was taken into custody.
Three people were killed and a four-year-old child was wounded in a shooting.
Six people were wounded in an early morning shooting at a block party/protest that was organized by a man to protest "inequitable narratives."
Five family members were injured after a gunman opened fire on their mobile home at night.
Four people were shot, one fatally, in the evening hours in the central part of the city.
A man shot and killed his in-laws, and wounded an 11-year-old boy sitting in a relative's car before committing suicide.
Four people were injured in a shooting at a gas station.
Four men were wounded in a drive-by shooting shortly before midnight.
Four people were wounded in the early morning at a night club. Two men were later arrested.

Police responding to a shots fired call found a car in the middle of an intersection between the Gwynn Oak and Howard Park neighborhoods with four men shot inside. Three of the men were pronounced dead at a hospital.
Two men were killed, and two women and a two-year-old were wounded at multiple crime scenes.

Art All Night shooting: Multiple gunmen wounded 17 people at the Art All Night festival. Five others were wounded when they were trampled by people around them. One of the suspected gunmen was shot and killed by police. Police suspect the shooting was gang-related.

Five men aged eighteen to twenty-six-years-old were found wounded in an east Germantown street shortly before midnight. A sixth man was found wounded in his apartment building from a stray bullet a half-block away.
Three teenagers and a boy were injured in a shooting.
Four people were shot, including a security guard, shortly after midnight after a fight broke out at a bar. One of the victims died from their injuries.
Police responding to shots fired at a senior living complex discovered a wounded woman, and two males and a woman deceased. It is believed one of the deceased males was the shooter.
A teenager was killed and three other people were injured in a drive-by shooting during a cookout. A 15-year-old was later charged with the killing.

Two bystanders including a seventeen-year-old were wounded shortly before midnight at an apartment complex. Two additional wounded were discovered later by police, who stated the shooting occurred after the individuals they had met to purchase guns from, turned on them and opened fire.
Six people were wounded after an incident at a liquor store escalated.
Four people were shot at a Quality Inn hotel near the pool in the Peterson neighborhood. A teen boy was found dead by responding police.
At a Walmart store, a man killed two people then wounded a police officer before being shot by police and arrested.
A gunman walked up to and wounded four people standing on the street.
A nineteen-year-old was killed and two nineteen-year-old and an eighteen-year-old were injured, when a car pulled up alongside their vehicle and opened fire on I-530.
Five people were wounded in a shooting at a candlelight vigil near the intersection in Sherman Park. The vigil was held for a 16-year-old who was killed at the same intersection earlier that day.
Five teenagers were shot by an attacker while they sat in a car in the Oceanway neighborhood. One of the teenagers died from their injuries.
During an attempted home invasion, shots were fired and four people were wounded.
Four people were injured in a shooting.
Two seventeen-year-olds were killed and a seventeen and eighteen year old wounded in a shooting in Point Breeze.

An SUV with four deceased adults was found in a local cornfield in Wheeler, Wisconsin. It was discovered later that the four victims were shot in Saint Paul following an argument at a bar with the shooter. The perpetrator's father followed his son in a vehicle on the way to Wheeler and then gave his son a ride home after his son abandoned the SUV in the cornfield.

Police officers responding to a disturbance at Northpark Mall were fired upon by a shooter, leaving two officers injured. The perpetrator then fled the scene westward where another shooting between officers and the shooter occurred, leaving another officer injured as well as the attacker. One of the officers, as well as the attacker, died at a hospital later the same day, while another officer died a few days later.
A man shot and killed his ex-girlfriends parents, and wounded her, before committing suicide in a murder–suicide.
Five people were injured in a shooting that took place in a cemetery.
One man was killed and two other adults and a sixteen-year-old were wounded while playing cards in an early morning drive-by shooting.
Four people were found wounded from a shooting.
Three people were shot in a car in northwest Knoxville, with a fourth person also being shot a short distance away.
Five people were shot at a party at a home rented through Airbnb.
A fight turned into a shooting that resulted in a 15-year-old being killed and four other people being injured.
Three teenagers, two fifteen-year-olds and a seventeen-year-old, and an adult were wounded in the Brookfield Village neighborhood in East Oakland. Police believe it to be a targeted shooting.
Two women were killed and four others wounded in a drive-by shooting that targeted a family birthday party.
Four people who were dining inside a seafood restaurant in the Phoenix Hill neighborhood were shot in a drive-by shooting.
A gunman shot six people, four fatally, before killing himself.
One person was killed and four were wounded in a drive-by shooting.
Police responding to a call of several people shot, found two adults and two teenagers aged thirteen and seventeen-years-old wounded in a townhouse complex.
Three people were found wounded on the street by police, and a fourth victim was located after he fled to the hospital. Two of the victims perished at the hospital.
Four people were shot in the Parkway and Cherry Point neighborhood in the early morning hours.
Gilroy Garlic Festival shooting: Sixteen people were shot, four fatally, including a gunman and two children, at the Gilroy Garlic Festival.

A 13-year-old boy was killed, and his mother, 8-year-old brother, and a bystander were wounded in a road rage incident after the shooter followed them to the parking lot of a dentist's office. The shooter was arrested.

A nineteen and seventeen-year-old were killed and two other teenagers were wounded, when a vehicle pulled up to the car that they were in and opened fire. Officers believe at least one person in the vehicle was the intended target.
Five teenagers were wounded at a party at a local shopping center.
In the early morning hours, an argument at a home in the Whittier neighborhood escalated into a shooting that killed one, and injured three.
Four people were wounded on two separate streets in connection with a large party.
Four people were injured in a shooting in the Bronx.
Seven people were wounded at a community gathering at a local community center. Eyewitnesses were split on how the shooting occurred.
A man was killed and three others injured in South Side drive-by shooting.
A fight between a group of people spiraled into a shooting that injured five teenagers, one of whom died at a hospital.
One man was killed and five were injured by an unknown perpetrator as the victims were preparing to shoot a rap video.
Four people were injured in a shooting after a verbal altercation. Three suspects were arrested.
Five people were wounded in an early morning shooting, with one later dying at a hospital.
A woman was killed and four adults and a teenager wounded in a West Pullman drive-by while walking as a group.
A fight at a party being hosted at an OYO Rooms hotel led to four people being shot shortly after midnight.
One woman and three men were wounded in a drive-by shooting outside of a Lawndale gas station.
After barricading himself and his four children in a home for nearly 24 hours, a man shot and wounded a police officer before killing the four children and himself.
Five people were shot, one fatally, at a restaurant in Morgan Park.
Responding officers discovered two wounded from an early morning shooting. Two others arrived were identified at the hospital.
Half an hour after midnight a man shot five people, killing two. The perpetrator escaped the scene of the shooting, leading to a manhunt.
Four people were shot and injured while standing outside of a bar/nightclub.
One person was killed and five others were injured after a fight in a bar moved outside and a member of one of the groups began shooting.
Four adults and a fourteen-year-old girl were injured at a block party when an unknown individual opened fire early in the morning.
Responding officers found four men wounded.
A shooting injured three, including a teenager, and killed a man in eastern Glendale.
One man was killed and three were injured after an altercation at an apartment complex. The suspect was later arrested.
Six people were injured by gunfire at a birthday party.
A drive by shooting injured three adults standing outside early in the morning. An eight-year-old boy was injured when a bullet entered his bedroom through a wall.

Deputies were called after a man got drunk and fired shots into the air. He then opened fire on the security guard and officers, before driving down the road, getting into a car accident and opening fire on those in the car. He wounded the security guards and three in the vehicle.

After a failed car chase to capture car thieves, the criminals crashed the car into the patrol car of another officer who hadn't participated in the earlier car chase. The occupants of the stolen car exited the vehicle and opened fire on the deputy, wounding him. The officer returned fire and wounded the two attackers. A bystander who was in an automotive shop nearby was struck in the leg by gunfire.
Thirteen people were shot, one fatally, at a playground in Brownsville.
A 14-year-old boy was killed and four other people were wounded at a party. A 14-year-old boy was arrested in connection to the shooting.
Shortly before midnight a group was walking down an alley toward a store, when they were approached by three men. One opened fire and killed two of the group and injured two others.
Six adults and a child were wounded in a drive-by shooting. The suspects attempted to flee the area but were hit by a MetroLink train.

Four people were shot when someone in a car opened fire on another car on I-75, wounding three people inside. Another car, whose occupants were not the intended target, was also shot, and one person inside was injured. A fifth victim was also struck by gunfire but was not injured.
Officers responded to a call at a residence and discovered three deceased victims, and one wounded male, resulting from a double murder–suicide.

Seven people were injured after gunfire broke out at a party. Several men arrived at the home and began to shoot, and an attendee at the party shot back. The police believe the incident was gang-related.
A man was killed and five others injured in an early morning shooting near a local pub.
Responding officers found one child deceased and two adults and another child injured.
A dispute between neighbors led to a shooting that injured seven, one fatally, near the Las Vegas Strip.

A man killed four people, including his father and brother, and wounded two more at a total of four different crime scenes across the San Fernando Valley. Two of the wounded later died, bringing the death toll to 4 people.
Two people were killed and two others were wounded after a shooting at a birthday party. The suspect was later taken into custody.
Four adults and a fifteen-year-old boy were wounded in a late night shooting in the Deep Ellum district.
Four people were wounded after two men got into an argument after one was seen arguing and pistol whipping a woman.
Four men were shot in the Walbrook neighborhood. One of the victims was found dead in an alleyway by responding police.
Two men were killed and two others were wounded after an argument between a group escalated into a shooting.
One person was killed and five others were injured in a drive-by shooting.
Four men were wounded by multiple shooters who fled the scene in the car they shot from.
After getting kicked out of a night club shortly after midnight, a man opened fire killed a man and wounded five women.

A man fatally shot his three children and the children's chaperone, before shooting himself, at a church during a supervised visit. A restraining order against the father prevented him from seeing his children, except for four-hour sessions, in which a friend of the mother had to be present.
A gunman opened fire on a group of people, wounding four, as they congregated outside of a gas station.
Four people were injured in a shooting at a house party.
A sixteen-year-old boy was killed and three other juveniles were wounded in Gateway Discovery Park.
Four people were wounded in a local park in the Southbridge neighborhood after a drive-by shooting.
An argument between two groups of people at a Dave and Buster's late Sunday night led to shooting that injured four. All of the victims were members of the two groups.
Four people were injured in a shooting, which was captured by surveillance video.
Four people were wounded after a gunman began shooting outside a high school graduation party.
A man engaged in a year-long dispute with neighbors, shot four of them as they sat on his porch. Three died and one was wounded, with the shooter later turning himself in.
A man opened fire after an argument at a local Black Pride festival, wounding five.
An argument at a business in the southeast part of the city led to four people being shot.
Six people were wounded in an overnight shooting.
Four or five gunmen killed one person and injured four others.
Three men and a woman were injured in a late night shooting, while in a large gathering.
Four men were injured in a shooting outside a rollerskating rink on Eight Mile Road in the west side.
Four people were shot in the southern part of the city, and one victim died at a hospital later the same day.
Four teenagers—between the ages of 14 and 18—were wounded in a shooting at a graduation party.
Three men were killed and a fourth was injured after a car pulled up alongside theirs and the occupant began shooting.
Three adults and a seventeen-year-old boy were injured in East Germantown in an evening shooting.
An adult and three teenagers were wounded at a local festival after two people got into an argument and one opened fire.
After the conclusion of a parade, a man fired at people in front of a store from his car, wounding several. Multiple people in the crowd fired back, seriously wounding the attacker.
Seven people were wounded in a shooting in Lincoln Park, after an argument between two groups escalated.

After an argument at a football game, a man drove a moped into the middle of the field and began to fire a gun. Multiple people then began firing at the shooter. Five people were injured in the exchange of gunshots.
Norfolk police said five people were shot on Wednesday night. One of the victims was a 1-month-old child. No suspect information is available at this time.
Four adults were wounded outside a catering hall in the Bronx after an argument escalated.
An exchange of gunfire between people in southwest Albuquerque led to four people being shot, and one victim dying from their injuries.
One woman was killed and three people were injured on a porch at a home in Garfield Park in Chicago's West Side.
One person was killed and three others were wounded by two gunmen in a drive-by shooting.
Four men were wounded in an evening shooting, with two being transported to the hospital in private vehicles.
Four adults were wounded at a family car show after two men opened fire on the crowd in suspected gang violence.

An argument between two men at a hookah bar east of the Las Vegas strip led to the two men opening fire on each other. The subsequent shooting resulted in the death of one, and injuries to thirteen others.
Five men in a vehicle were targeted by a shooter who killed one and injured three others.
One person was killed and six others were injured in a shooting. A suspect was taken into custody.
Four men were wounded after a vehicle pulled up and opened fire, with one of the wounded returning fire.
Firefighters discovered a husband and wife and two children deceased when responding to a house fire. Family members believe the family had been dead for days before the fire.
A shooter inside a car opened fire on the occupants of another car near the entrance of the Mall of Louisiana, killing two of the people inside, and wounding the other two.
A man opened fire on his co-workers at a moving company, injuring four, after a disagreement escalated. The suspect was later arrested.
Five people were injured in a shooting at an outdoor gathering.
A man was killed and three others wounded, in an early morning shooting.
A man fired into a crowd of people that were fighting in the early morning. He wounded seven and turned himself in the next day.
Four people were shot and killed in a murder–suicide, including two children in northeastern Granbury.
One person was killed and three were wounded in an apartment complex.
A man killed a woman and two of her daughters, and injured her husband and her third daughter, when he shot them at their home. He has been arrested.
Four people were wounded in an evening shooting.

A former Marine sharpshooter shot and killed three adults, an infant, and a dog and wounded a child inside and outside a home, before engaging in a shootout with police. The shooter was eventually injured in the gunfight and then apprehended.
A shooter opened fire on three people inside a car in the Serna Station neighborhood. A fourth person who was not targeted by the shooter was also struck by gunfire.
Four people were wounded in a shooting after a potential drug deal turns deadly.

2018 Scottsdale shootings: Over the course of several days (May 30, 2018 to June 4, 2018), a man killed a forensic psychologist, two paralegals, a counselor, and a couple from whom he took a handgun. The suspect killed himself when police began closing in on him.
A man was killed and four others including a teenage boy were wounded in a night shooting.
Three adults and a teenager were wounded after an argument outside a Mt. Washington home. The victims went inside, before the suspect fired through the door.

A man shot another man at a home in northern Claxton. When two family members of the victim arrived on the scene to check on him, the shooter shot them in their car, and was promptly shot by responding police.
A man attempted to use a gun to demand methadone, then killed one and wounded two before being killed by police in a shootout.
Four people were injured in a shooting on the bank of the Red River.
Seven people were wounded when gunfire erupted while a large crowd was gathered outside a gas station early in the morning.
Two people were killed and two injured after an argument inside a strip mall store escalated. Three people were arrested and one went on the run.

A man ambushed another man, some of his family members, and a neighbor who was a police officer in the victim's backyard due to a feud with his target. The deputy, who was not shot, returned fire and killed the shooter.
Seven people were wounded in a shooting during a neighborhood basketball game.
A fight in a nightclub spilled into the parking lot and resulted in a shooting that killed one person and injured three others.
A man was killed and three others wounded in a housing complex in Brooklyn in the early morning.
Responding officers found four people injured, with one later dying at the hospital.
Multiple shooters opened fire outside a funeral home hosting a memorial for a gun violence victim in the West Side neighborhood, resulting in the death of a man, and injuries to three others.
One person was killed and four were wounded in a drive-by shooting in Chicago's South Side.
A shooting broke out after a man tried to rob a group of people playing dice. Four people were injured by gunshots. Two men were arrested.
A nineteen-year-old man was killed and two men and two women injured in an early morning shooting at a party.
Six people were found injured in Northwest DC, with three later dying at a hospital.
A shooting at a grocery store in the Prospect Hill neighborhood left four injured, including a teenager.
Four suspects got into a gunfight, wounding four teenagers in a common area at an apartment complex.
Four people were wounded in a shooting at a block party.
Four men were wounded at a party outside an apartment complex when a fight escalated early in the morning.
A teenager was killed and four others injured while attending a block party.
Four people were shot in a car in southeast Portland, with the female driver being killed. Among the injured were two young children.
Two people were killed and two children—16 and 10-years-old, were wounded after a domestic dispute escalated.
Two suspects fired shots into a nightclub, killing one person and wounding seven others.
Four men were wounded standing outside a business in the Englewood neighborhood, in an afternoon drive-by shooting.
A teenager shot four people on the street in Homewood South.
A child was killed in a drive-by shooting targeting a group of people playing basketball at a park. Four others were injured.
Four perpetrators wounded four men in a shooting outside of a 7-Eleven store.

Santa Fe High School shooting: A student at Santa Fe High School shot and killed ten people and wounded fourteen others. Explosive devices were also found, but they were not detonated. The suspect was taken into custody by police.

Early in the morning responding officers found three wounded individuals at a home near Pikes Peak International Raceway. Three more wounded were identified at a local hospital and some of the wounded are teenagers. Officers believe the shooting happened at a house party.
Five people were injured in a drive-by shooting in Lawndale shortly after midnight.

Normandale Park shooting: Near an racial justice protest, a man allegedly confronted a group of protestors and engaged in an argument with them, before pulling out a gun and opening fire, killing one and wounding four others. One of the people in the group allegedly returned fire and wounded the perpetrator.
Six people were shot, two fatally, while in a car at a gas station. Police are looking for two suspects.
A man wounded his ex-wife and killed their three children and his ex-wife's boyfriend before killing himself in a murder–suicide.
Shortly before midnight one man was killed and three others injured.
Four adults were wounded in an early morning shooting during an outdoor party.
A shooter opened fire in the food court of University Mall, shooting and injuring a woman. Three others were injured by shrapnel or bullet fragments.
Four people were wounded in a shooting after a potential argument escalated.
Four men were wounded in a shooting near a playground.
One person was killed and three wounded after an early morning shooting near the Allison Bonnet Memorial Drive.
A woman was killed and three others injured in an apartment complex close to US Highway 290 in East Austin.
An argument at a party being held at an abandoned building led to a shooting that injured fourteen, and killed two.
Four people were wounded in an early morning shooting in Chicago's Englewood neighborhood.
A shooter fired into a home, killing a five-year-old girl and her parents, and wounding two other family members.
A gun fight wounded two adults and two seventeen-year-olds in West Philadelphia.
One person was killed and three injured outside a shoe store in a strip mall, after two men exited a car and opened fire.
A man shot seven people outside a bar in the early morning hours in a targeted shooting perpetrated against one of the victims.
Four people were discovered wounded in a parking lot in the downtown area.
A man opened fire at a block party, possibly after a fight over a dice game, wounding four people. The suspect was arrested.
Five adults and a seventeen-year-old were wounded after a man stepped out of a vehicle and opened fire on a large gathering. The shooting took place in Gresham in the South Side.
Four people were wounded after shooters opened fire on them across the street while they were standing outside a deli.

Four men were shot at a Campus Apartments complex near North Carolina Central University and Duke University. Two were found dead by responding police, and none of the victims were students of either school.
Four people were discovered wounded by police, who responded to a shots fired call; the victims had driven away from the initial scene.
A man killed one teenage boy and wounded three others. One of the wounded boys died in the hospital several days later.
A man was killed and four others wounded including a fifteen-year-old in the Strawberry Mansion neighborhood.
A man killed one person and wounded two others before kidnapping a woman and infant. He later killed the woman and left the baby alive in the stolen vehicle and is still on the run.
Four bystanders, including a teen girl, were shot when two men shot at each other outside a RiteAid drugstore in the East Germantown neighborhood.
After a dispute over fireworks, a man shot into a crowd and injured a 12-year-old child and a woman, then barricaded himself in his home. Police discovered him and a woman deceased in the home.
Seven people were wounded in a shooting.
A car drove up to a Ravenswood Public Housing building in Queens and opened fire. A seventeen-year-old boy and three adults were wounded.
A man killed two people and wounded three others in a mobile home park, before being killed by responding police.
During a biker event at a nightclub in the MacGregor neighborhood, an argument led to a shootout between patrons, which injured five people. Among the wounded was the club's bouncer.
Four people were shot in a McDonald's parking lot after a dispute involving a rideshare vehicle.
Four people were injured by gunfire in a shooting following a fight at a birthday party.
Four people were wounded in the early morning at a large gathering in Twin Sisters Park.
Five people were wounded in an early morning drive by shooting on Jefferson Street.
Three men were wounded, and one was killed, in an ambush-style shooting in the afternoon. Two sedans pulled up alongside them on the street and opened fire.
A gunman opened fire — injuring four people in the East New York neighborhood.
Two children and two adults were injured when shooters fired at them from two cars.
Two people were killed and two people were wounded in a shooting late at night before the car they were in crashed.
Three adults were wounded and one was killed near Rainbow Boulevard.
Four men were shot in northeast Joliet in the evening. One of the men was found dead by responding police.
Five people were wounded in a shooting in Chicago's Woodlawn community.
Four police officers were injured in a shootout while trying to execute a search warrant, either by gunfire or from shrapnel from explosives in the home. The suspect was killed.
Five people were wounded at Dove Park in an evening drive-by shooting.
An adult and three teenagers were wounded.
Officers responding to an early morning shots fired call engaged in a foot chase with an armed man who had shot five people. After an attempted negotiation, he committed suicide.
One person died and three were wounded in a shooting.
Four people were injured in a suspected drive-by shooting outside an apartment complex.
Four men were wounded in an early morning shooting in Brooklyn. The suspected gunman fled in a car after opening fire.
Responding officers found two wounded men, a wounded teenager and two other adults were later found at hospitals.
Outside an Italian restaurant hosting a party by Justin Bieber, a fight between a group of men escalated when a shooter opened fire, wounding four, including musician Kodak Black.

Four people were found deceased at a home in an apparent murder–suicide. The deaths consisted of two young males, and one middle aged female, not including the perpetrator who killed himself afterwards.
Four people were wounded in a shooting.
A man is accused of killing his ex-girlfriend, a man in her home, and a neighbor and wounding two others. He was later arrested after hiding in the surrounding woods.
Two groups got into an argument near Belmont Park and a man opened fire, wounding four people.
In the early morning hours, four people were shot in eastern Little Rock, with one person succumbing to their injuries.
Six people were wounded in Boston's Roxbury neighborhood.
Two men approached a group of people and wounded four people. A fifth victim was shot and wounded several blocks away. Police believe the first attack was gang-related.
Five people were injured, one critically, in a shooting caused by a dispute at a flea market. A security guard returned fire.
Four adults were wounded in Douglas Park while attending a large gathering.
An argument outside a hookah bar in the early morning hours escalated when a shooter opened fire, wounding four, and killing one.
One man was killed and three were wounded, after a suspect opened fire from a vehicle.
After a fight and theft from the bar and a tip jar, private security shut down a party. As the guests left, several weapons were fired and four people were injured.
One person died at the scene and one later at the hospital with nine others wounded in an early morning shooting.

After a football game at a high school, a civilian was injured in a drive-by shooting. Police fired back, which district attorney Jack Stollsteimer says likely hit four people, including an eight-year-old girl who was killed.
A driver shot at another car, wounding four people inside in northwest Springfield.
Four people, including a 15-year-old girl were wounded, after two perpetrators opened fire in the Historic South-Central neighborhood.
Two people were killed and four were injured after they were shot while traveling in a car by a gunman in another car.
An eighteen-year-old was killed and three others wounded after a disturbance occurred at a large gathering.
Two adults and two children were shot, with an adult and child later dying from their injuries.

Responding to a call of a woman being shot, a shooter ambushed a responding officer and shot him several times. As a man fled the home with a baby, and officers attempted to aid in protecting the baby, the shooter shot four more officers, with four more being injured by bullet shrapnel. The shooter then barricaded himself inside the home, and was later found dead, along with a female victim.
Four people were wounded after an argument escalated.
Five people were injured in a shooting. A suspect was arrested.
Two men were killed and five others were wounded in a shooting shortly after an earlier shooting.
Four men were found injured in the West Hollywood neighborhood.

A chance encounter between two rival gangs at an apartment complex in Southwest Fresno escalated into a shootout, with four gang members being shot, including a teenager. Two men died from their injuries.
One person was killed and three were injured after gunfire erupted at an Independence Day celebration.
Four people were injured in a shooting.
Responding officers found a man wounded shortly after midnight, who later died at the hospital. Three others arrived by private vehicles to the hospital.
Seven people were wounded just after midnight when two people opened fire at one another.
A shooter fired at a crowd gathered to celebrate the life of a gun violence victim and wounded four, including a child and a teenager, in the Montgomery Place neighborhood.
The perpetrator shot and killed his sister and three others at a housewarming party. He later died at a hospital.
A shooting at a house party wounded four people.
Four people were wounded at a large birthday party in the parking lot.
A teenager and three adults were wounded in a drive by shooting in Uptown.
In the early morning hours, a fight at a bar led to a patron being removed from the building, after which the patron opened fire from outside the bar and wounded four other patrons.
A 16-year-old, 12-year-old and an adult were injured when an argument over fireworks escalated. The perpetrator was shot by a by-stander.
A man shot at a group of people from a car, killing one and wounding four. He and the driver of the car were later arrested.
Four adults and a sixteen-year-old boy were injured shortly before midnight at a large block party when a group on motorcycles arrived and opened fire.
A man was killed and three adults and a teenager were wounded in East Garfield Park, about four hours after a previous mass shooting.
A physical altercation in the early morning hours at a Bowlero bowling alley led to a shooting, with five people being wounded.
Four people were injured in a drive-by shooting just before midnight near a local food store.
Six people were wounded after guns were fired following an argument at a housing complex. Three people were arrested.
Five people were wounded shortly before midnight.
A SIU student was killed and three other people wounded at a party hosted at a private residence.

A man shot four of his own family members, three fatally, in Corsicana before driving to Frost where he shot three more of his own family, killing two, including a child. After his vehicle was remotely shut off via a vehicle monitoring service, the Corsicana SWAT team closed in on his location. Before they could reach him, the shooter shot himself, and later died from his injuries.
Four women were injured after a suspect opened fire on them, two were discovered by police, the others privately entered the hospital.
One person was killed and four were wounded following a shooting outside of a Brooklyn apartment complex.

Two men and two women were killed in a home, with one of the women killed identified as the shooter's former fiancée. The shooter boasted about the killings on social media and text messages before being arrested.
Five men were wounded at a vigil for a man that had been killed in the same location earlier in the day.
Four people were shot in southern Las Cruces, with two teenagers requiring medical evacuation via helicopter to El Paso.
A 12-year-old boy and two adults were injured in a shooting outside of an apartment complex.
Five people were injured in a shooting.
One man was killed and five injured after a dice game grew violent shortly before midnight.
One person was killed and three wounded in an early morning shooting.
Five people, including a college student at nearby Virginia Tech, which went on lockdown, were shot at a hookah lounge. One person succumbed to their injuries.
Five people were wounded after a fight escalated in a mobile home park after a BBQ.
A man pulled out a gun after being punched during an after-party at a club and wounded four people.
Officers arrived at a large gathering early in the morning to disperse it. While doing so shots were fired in the apartment complex's parking lot. Two men were killed and three others wounded.
Four people were wounded in an East Garfield Park drive-by.

Five people were wounded, one fatally, by a shooter in a Greyhound bus. The shooter was later apprehended by police at a nearby Walmart after he got into a physical altercation with a customer and took off all his clothes.
Two teenagers were killed and two were wounded in a drive-by shooting near a playground.
Four people were injured in a drive-by shooting.
Three women and one man were wounded late at night on Lenox Avenue in Harlem.
A man was killed and five others wounded while standing in a Calumet Heights parking lot, after two men opened fire from an alley.

A fight between two teenage girls about a Facebook post during a basketball game at Rufus King International High School escalated when a man opened fire, wounding four teenage girls, and an adult woman.
Six people were shot at a house party.
A man shot and wounded two people at an apartment complex. Two more people were wounded by gunfire while trying to disarm the shooter. The shooter was arrested.
A woman was killed and three others wounded in a drive by shooting in the early morning.
One person died and three were injured after a shooting.
Four people were shot at a motel in the late evening hours. Two of the victims were shot in the motel parking lot, while the other two were shot in their rooms.
Seven people were injured in a shooting outside of a night club after a fight escalated.
Two people were killed and two others were injured in a shooting in a parking lot outside a motorcycle club.
An eighteen-year-old was killed and four others wounded shortly after midnight.
Four people were shot in a Bronzeville business.

Two cars engaged in a running gun battle. Four people, including two teenagers, were shot in one of the cars, with a fifth also being wounded in the other car. An adult passenger in the first vehicle was killed.
Police discovered two people wounded, while an additional two were self-transported to area hospitals.
A man killed one person and wounded three others in a shooting. He was later arrested by police.

Five people were wounded shortly after midnight outside of a warehouse in the Harbor Gateway neighborhood. The shooting occurred after an argument escalated, and an additional person was injured attempting to climb a fence.
A drive-by shooting outside a barbershop killed one and wounded four.
Four people were shot in the early morning hours at a club. A man was found dead by responding police.
Five people were wounded after gunfire broke out at a gathering in the Near West Side neighborhood.
A man killed one person and injured three others in a shooting at a nightclub. He was later arrested by police.
Ten people were injured in a drive-by shooting during a family gathering in a park.
A man was killed and three others wounded in an evening shooting.
Four people were shot at a bar during the late evening hours in the Polo Grounds neighborhood.
Seven people were wounded during a drive-by shooting involving two vehicles.
Five were injured in a shooting following an argument at a party.
Six people were wounded in the early morning after a large gathering turned violent near a shopping center.
A teenager was arrested for allegedly shooting four people on a basketball court, killing a man and wounding three teenagers.

Four men were shot near an intersection in the Kingsway East neighborhood, with two found dead at the scene. Another man died at a hospital, and the surviving victim ran to a nearby convenience store for help.
Four people were wounded by gunfire that erupted on a street.
Four people were injured after men stepped out of a truck and began shooting at them.

2020 Washington, D.C. block party shooting: A 17-year-old boy was killed and 21 others injured, including an off-duty police officer, at a party in the southeastern section of the nation's capital. Police are looking for three suspects.
Two people, including a 10-year-old girl, were killed, and four wounded after a shooting.
An argument escalated into a shooting outside a sports bar in the Vine City neighborhood shortly after midnight, with one person being fatally shot, and three others being injured by gunfire.
Five people were wounded in a shooting, after police break up a house party.
Three people were killed and one was wounded after being shot in a home. A suspect was later taken into custody by police.
Four people were wounded in the evening, two of the victims drove away and later crashed outside a local bank.
Four men were wounded after a shooting in Playa del Ray.
A man shot his wife and two children in a murder–suicide at his home.
Five people were wounded in a shooting.
Four people were injured in a shooting.
Four men were wounded being a gas station shortly before midnight. The men were playing dice, when a gunman walked up, shot them and fled on foot.
A man was killed and three injured in a shooting.
Two people were fatally shot at a Shell gas station, with three others being wounded.
Seven people were wounded, two critically, in a drive-by shooting in the Old Fourth Ward neighborhood.
After a domestic issue, a man went on a shooting spree that resulted in one death and five people being injured by gunfire. The man was arrested.
Shortly before midnight a man was killed and four others wounded in the city's north side.
Five men were wounded in a drive-by shooting outside a grocery store in Brooklyn.
Five people were shot at a Days Inn hotel in the Forest Hills neighborhood. A woman later succumbed to her injuries.
One man was killed and three others, including a boy, were wounded in a home invasion.
Nashville Waffle House shooting: A gunman entered a Waffle House, where he killed four people and injured two others. He was later taken into custody.
A pregnant woman, three teenagers and two other women were wounded. They were a part of a large BBQ gathering at a public park.
Five women and three men were wounded outside a housing project in Brooklyn shortly after midnight.
Six people were found by police shot to death in a home after being called there for a welfare check in the Park West neighborhood.
A four-hour standoff ends after a man kills four people then himself.
A man killed two people and wounded two others after being kicked out of a party.
Five men were wounded at a house party which was detected by the city's gunshot detection system. Prior a woman from the same party was stabbed.
A man was killed and three others injured outside a local bar.

Four people were fatally shot at a birthday party at a home in the morning in an ambush-style attack. A fifth person was shot but survived their injuries. The woman whose birthday was being celebrated, along with her older sister, were among the deceased.
Two people were killed and two were wounded in a shooting at an apartment complex. One of the victims later died at the hospital from their injuries.
A gunman shot six men standing near each, killing one and injuring five.

A man was killed and five people, including an off-duty Birmingham Police officer, were wounded at a motorcycle club in Ensley. The shooting was reported to be due to an altercation escalating, with some of the victims innocent bystanders.
Three people were killed and two injured after a fight escalated in the parking lot of a local sports bar on the East Side, by a man who drew a long gun and shot into the air.

Four people were shot by an occupant in an approaching vehicle outside an apartment complex in the South End neighborhood while they were in two vehicles. Two of the victims drove away together to Tacoma, where one of them was found dead by police.
Five people were wounded in a drive-by shooting outside of a local motorcycle club.
A man killed a mother and two of her children, wounded her other three children, and then killed himself.
A 18-year-old man was killed and a 22-year-old, 28-year-old, and 29-year-old were injured in a drive by shooting involving multiple suspected perpetrators.
Three men and a woman were wounded standing outside a home shortly after midnight.
Four people were wounded after a drive-by shooting at a bar. An off-duty officer returned fire, killing one of the suspects.
One person was killed and three others were injured after a drive-by shooting at a party.
Six people in a tattoo parlor were injured when they were shot at by a person in a pickup truck outside the business.
A man was killed and three others injured while standing outside a house party.
Four adults and a teenager were wounded outside a nightclub shortly after midnight.
Three men, including an on-duty violence-prevention worker, were fatally shot in the Milton-Monford neighborhood. Another man who was shot survived his injuries.
One person was killed and ten were injured after the perpetrator opened fire on a patrons at a local bar.
Four people were injured in a shooting outside an apartment complex.
An 8-year-old boy and three men were wounded in the North Lawndale neighborhood. The shooter exited a vehicle and opened fire on the group while they were standing on the sidewalk.
A man was killed and three adults and a child wounded in a strip mall parking lot in the early morning.
Four men were injured when a vehicle approached them and multiple occupants opened fire upon them. The victims returned fire, and the attackers fled.
Four men were wounded by gunfire in an overnight shooting.
Several people fired hundreds of rounds outside of a bar, killing one person and injuring three others. Three men were arrested.
Four people were wounded in Garner Park during a memorial service for a recently deceased individual. Over 300 people were gathered when gunfire broke out and a fifth person was injured fleeing.
Four men were wounded in Brooklyn shortly after midnight.

After a man was escorted out of a bar for assaulting his female companion, he drove away, and later returned with a gun and opened fire on the bar's security guards, with three female patrons and one security guard being wounded. A security guard inside the bar returned fire, and killed the shooter.
Two adults and two children were injured in a shooting at Buckroe Beach.
Two people were killed and two were wounded in a shooting in the Liberty City neighborhood of Miami.
Four men were wounded in an evening shooting.
Responding officers found four wounded in the early morning.
Four people were shot at a Martin Luther King Jr. Day gathering in the Coliseum Willow Park neighborhood.
A gunman opened fire on a crowd, killing a 19-year-old man and wounding four others.
Four people were wounded in a shooting.
A woman was killed and four others were injured at a rented mansion house party. The home was on the famed Mulholland Drive in the Beverly Crest neighborhood.
One person was killed and six teenagers wounded after a fight broke out at a local park shortly after midnight.
Four people, including two teens, were shot in the Benjamin Van Clark Park neighborhood. A woman died from her injuries, and five vehicles were struck by gunfire.
Four people were shot, one fatally, at a house on the city's west side.
One person was killed and three others were injured in a shooting.
A woman was killed and two adults and a 17-year-old were injured near the former ABB manufacturing plant. The plant was the scene of a mass shooting in 2010.
A man opened fire on a group playing a dice game outside a local bar. One man was killed and four injured.
One person was killed, and five others injured, after two men shot at one another inside a club.
Five people were wounded in a drive-by shooting.
Two people were killed and two others were injured in a shooting.
A man was killed and five others injured after an early morning shooting at a large gathering at a warehouse.
Two men, identified as rap-artists connected to the Wu-Tang Clan, were killed and four others wounded, in a potential drive-by shooting.
Four women were shot in a parked car in the early morning hours. The driver then drove them all to a hospital.
Four people, including a pregnant woman, were wounded in a shooting outside of the Parkway Garden Homes apartment complex.
YouTube headquarters shooting: A woman approached an outdoor patio at YouTube Headquarters and wounded three people before committing suicide, a fourth person was injured in the evacuation.
Four people were wounded after a shooter opened fire on a large crowd watching a basketball game at St. Mary's Park in the Bronx.
A woman and teenager were killed and two other individuals wounded in an evening shooting.
A shooting broke out just before the start of a rap concert at W.O.W. Hall, resulting in six injuries.
Ten people were injured from gunfire outside of a nightclub.
One person was killed and three others were wounded in a drive-by shooting outside of a home.
Four women were injured with gun fire in the early morning. A fifth woman was stabbed multiple times.
Two teenagers were killed and four others injured at a late-night party at a city park.
A man shot three people in southern Augusta, two fatally, before committing suicide.
One man was killed and six others were injured after gunfire broke out in two separate locations in the downtown area.
A fifteen-year-old was killed and four other people were wounded in a shooting at a spring break party.
Four adults and a 10-year-old child were wounded after multiple heavily armed shooters opened fire on males in a specific block.

A woman was killed and five others were injured in a shooting on Irma Street near the Mattapan/Dorchester border. Police arrived at the scene at about 12:30 a.m. and pronounced the woman dead. On August 24, police charged a 37-year-old man with murder in connection to the shooting.
Three men and a woman were shot inside of a rental hall in the Canarsie section of Brooklyn.
2019 Dallas courthouse shooting: One person was superficially injured and the perpetrator was killed in a shooting next to the Earle Cabell Federal Building.
Five people were injured in a shooting at a house party.
A man was killed and four others, two men and two women, were injured at a backyard BBQ. Responding officers arrested two men fleeing from the scene.
A security guard and four others were wounded after a man got into an argument with two security guards outside a club on the South Side.

Four people were wounded at the Parkway Garden Homes apartment complex in the Greater Grand Crossing neighborhood on the South Side, while standing on the sidewalk. A man approached them and opened fire before fleeing.
Four people were injured from gunfire, after getting into an altercation with another motorist.
Five people were wounded in a drive-by shooting.
Two men were killed and two adults and an infant were injured. A man entered a home where a child's birthday party was ongoing and opened fire. Two guests returned fire and were among the injured.
Five people were shot in the early morning on Bourbon Street. This was the second weekend in a row with a mass shooting in the city.

A gunman opened fire at a large party in South Los Angeles, wounding five people, while another party-goer returned fire and wounded the shooter. The shooter fled in a vehicle, which later crashed, and died at a hospital.
Five people were wounded in the parking lot of an apartment complex.
One person was killed and three others were injured in a shooting at an apartment complex. One person was arrested.
A 16-year-old was killed and three adults and a girl were wounded at a large gathering in the Westwood neighborhood.
A man was killed and five others wounded after a fight in a night club escalated out of the club and into the parking lot.
A man was killed, and six others, including four bystanders, were wounded inside a bowling alley after an argument escalated. The shooter fled afterwards.
One person was killed and seven were injured at a graduation party. All of the victims are between 15 and 17 years of age.
Four people were wounded in a shooting inside a business.
Four men were injured after a shooting at an entrance to I-85 South.
Two men were arguing outside a lounge on the South Side, before it escalated. One of the two was killed, and the other along with five bystanders was injured.
Four people were wounded outside a nightclub after an argument between two people escalated.
Five men and two women were discovered shot near a liquor store by police. One of the men later died at the hospital.
Four people were injured in a drive-by shooting directed at a traveling rap group. The shooting may have been gang-related.
A woman was killed and three men were wounded in an evening shooting.
Two men were killed and three wounded at an outdoor event space in Brooklyn shortly after midnight.
Responding officers found two people dead, and at least two injured, at an apartment complex in the early morning.
Six people were shot in a drive-by shooting while standing in the street after a party.
A police officer, the suspect, and four others were all wounded by gunfire. One of the wounded victims later died of his injuries.
Five men were wounded after a potentially gang related shooting occurred behind a U-Gas Station. A witness likened the amount of gunfire to the Iraq war.
Three men and a woman were wounded shortly after midnight.
A gunman opened fire outside a club, killing one, and wounding three others.
Four people were wounded in a drive-by shooting outside of a nightclub.
Seven people were injured in a shooting in a nightclub.
A man opened fire at a gas station while screaming at passersby. He wounded five people before he was arrested.
