Four men were wounded in a drive-by shooting.
One teen was shot to death, while three other teens were injured while sitting in a car at a gas station.
Three relatives, two children and two adults, were found dead from gunshot wounds in a house.
Four men were wounded in a shooting in a strip club, which seemed to stem from an earlier incident at a different nightclub.
Three men and a woman were injured while standing outside and a person opened fire from a car.
Four people were wounded in an early morning shooting in the Neon District.
Two men were found deceased in a crashed car with multiple gunshots. Two other adults in the backseat were wounded.
An adult male was killed at a party in a rented Airbnb; a teenager and two other adults were injured.
Four people were injured in a drive-by shooting. Two people were later arrested.
Three men were killed and a third injured after an afternoon dispute escalated between two groups of people.
Four people, two on the side walk and two in a vehicle, were wounded in a drive-by shooting in  West Nashville.
An altercation led to a shooting at an apartment complex. Two people were killed, and another was wounded, after bullets went through a wall. A fourth person was injured in another apartment.
Police responded to a scene and discovered two men deceased and two others injured.
Four people were injured when shots were fired through the garage door of the garage they were in.
A man killed his wife and three children, aged 12, 10 and 6-years-old, and then himself in an apparent murder-suicide.
Four adults were wounded a block away from Temple University Hospital.
Two women were killed, and three others wounded, in an early morning shooting.
Four people were wounded in an overnight shooting; the victims were self-transported to the hospital for treatment.
Three people were wounded and one other was fatally injured in a nightclub shooting following a verbal argument.
A 17-year-old and a woman were killed and two men were injured in a shooting.
A woman was killed and three others injured in the early morning in a home. Three men walked to the side of the home and shot repeatedly through the windows and walls.
A teenager was killed, and three adults and another teenager were wounded, in a shooting near Temple University.
One was killed and three others were injured in a shooting at a nightclub.
Six people were wounded when a man began shooting at a house party. He was arrested.
Four men were injured in the evening.
Two adults and a child were killed and a child wounded in a home. The shooter was arrested in Florida shortly after.
A shooter opened fire outside a nightclub, and wounded five.
Four people were injured in a shooting after a dispute.
Five people were injured in a shooting following an argument at a party.
A 17-year-old was killed and two adults and a 12-year-old injured at Steel Lake Park. A woman reportedly opened fire after an argument.
Nine people were wounded in the early morning at a local dance studio.

After officers were dispatched to respond to a domestic dispute at a home and they were en route, the call was upgraded to shots fired. Upon arriving, officers found a man had killed himself after shooting three people, including two children.
One person was killed and three wounded, after the perpetrator opened fire on a crowd gathered in Kerruish Park.

Yountville Shooting: A man entered the Veterans Home of California and held three staff members hostage. He killed the three staff members (and the unborn child of one of the staff members, who was pregnant) before killing himself in a murder–suicide.
Five people were sitting on a porch in the evening when one was killed and four injured in a drive-by shooting.
Five adults were wounded in an early morning shooting near Bourbon Street.
A man was killed, and three others wounded, in a shooting in a parking lot in the early morning.
Five people were killed after the perpetrator opened fire on the Yakama Indian Reservation.
A man killed three people and injured one other in a shooting at a restaurant and bar. He was arrested two days later.
Four people were injured in the early morning after at least two semi-automatic handguns were fired at a large house party.
A teenager was killed and two teenagers and an adult were wounded by a teenager in the Central Business District. He was turned in by a family member.
Four people were wounded at a shooting at a New Years party shortly after midnight.
Four people were wounded in the Humbdolt neighborhood after an altercation with the suspect.
A man entered a restaurant and killed the restaurant's owner and wounded three others. He was later taken into custody by police.
Four people were injured shortly after midnight when someone opened fire during the Rude Boyz Annual Trail Ride. The gathering was held at Durango's Canyon.
A man was killed and three wounded in an early morning shooting. Five suspects were later arrested.
Two adults were killed, and two wounded, in an early morning shooting in the LoDo district.
Five people were taken to the hospital after the suspect fired shots at the ground, indirectly wounding them.
One man was killed and four other people were injured in a shooting at a party.

One person was killed and three others were injured when two men opened fire in a restaurant. One man was charged with open murder, three counts of assault with intent to murder and multiple weapons charges. The other man was charged with careless discharge of a firearm.
Five people were wounded in the parking lot of a Popeyes restaurant in the early morning.
Four adults were wounded in the early morning in a shooting at a local bar.
One man was killed and three others wounded when a secondary vehicle pulled up next to vehicle and opened fire on Lake Shore Drive.
Four people were injured in a shooting.
Responding officers to a large gathering in the early morning found a man dead. Three additional victims were transported in private vehicles to the hospital.
Five people were wounded in an early morning shooting outside a local bar, and one died later at the hospital. An argument escalated causing a gunfight between multiple people.
A teenager opened fire at a soccer park, wounding an 11-year-old boy and three others.
One person was killed and three were injured in a shooting or series of shootings in a close vicinity in Brooklyn.

Officers responded to I-64 West in the early morning after calls of shots fired by a moving vehicle. They found four individuals shot, with one dead, in a crashed car. A fifth individual was wounded when the car crashed.
Four adults were wounded in an early morning shooting while at a gathering in Jackson Park on the South Side.
One person was killed and three were critically injured in an overnight shooting.
Four people were wounded after being shot by at least three shooters.
A woman and three men were wounded near a local restaurant.
Two people were wounded and two killed at a large public gathering.
An adult male and three teenagers were wounded in a shooting in the Austin community of Chicago.

A man shot and killed the mother of his child and another woman who was sitting with her in a car at a gas station. He then killed another man at the gas station before returning home and killing his cousin. After being urged by his mother to turn himself in to police, the suspect killed himself.
Officers responded from a traffic stop after hearing gunfire. They discovered seven people wounded at a large house party after a man armed with a semi-automatic weapon arrived and opened fire.
Ten people, including seven bystanders, were wounded in a night-time gang shooting outside a laundromat. The incident took place in North Corona, Queens.
Four men were wounded in two separate locations near Northwestern University's Gold Coast campus.
One person was killed and three were injured after a drug deal.
Six people were shot at a party of over 1,000 people following the filming of a music video in a parking lot.
Three adults and two children were wounded outside a funeral home. It is believed an argument escalated inside the building prior.
Police discovered three individuals wounded after responding to a shooting; an additional two were transported via personal vehicles to the hospital.
Five people were injured in a shooting outside a Texas Roadhouse.

A seven-year-old girl, a sixteen-month boy and two adults were shot by a passing vehicle while getting out of a car. The girl was declared brain dead at the hospital, causing the shooting to be declared a homicide.
Responding officers found five people wounded in an evening shooting.
Three men and a woman were injured after a suspect opened fire at a block party.
One person was killed and seven others were injured at a party in what police suspect to be a gang-related shooting.
Two men were killed and two woman and a man were wounded in the Park Hill neighborhood.
A feud between the occupants of two vehicles escalated into gunfire injuring three adults and a child.
Five men were wounded in a shooting at a car wash.
Five people were wounded in a shooting outside a nightclub.
Three men and a woman were injured shortly before midnight. A man was denied entry at a local bar, retrieved an assault-type weapon from his car, and shot into the building.

After an argument a man shot and killed his parents. He called 911, and stated he wished to turn himself in, but opened fire at responding officers wounding two. He fled the scene in a vehicle that he crashed and was discovered dead due to a self inflicted gunshot wound.
2019 Virginia Beach shooting: A gunman killed 12 people and injured four others at a city public works building. The gunman died at the scene after being shot by police.
One person was killed and three were injured inside a home. The man who died had been receiving threats after falling out with a gang. Two people were arrested.

Two adults were killed and two teenagers, aged seventeen and eighteen, were injured in an early morning shooting. The group were ambushed by two shooters after arriving at an AirBnb house party in a rideshare.
Five people were wounded in an afternoon shooting, with one later dying at the hospital.
Five people were wounded after a vehicle pulled up to a large gathering and opened fire.

Stoneman Douglas High School shooting: A former student of Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School entered the school, killed seventeen people, and wounded seventeen others. He was taken into custody by police.
One man was killed and three others injured in the early morning. Officers are investigating if the individuals were a part of an announced party for that night.
Four adults were wounded in a shooting in Southeast DC.
A man shot three employees at a local plumbing company, killing one before exchanging gunfire with a sheriff's deputy, also injuring him before committing suicide.
A series of shootings left three people dead and five others wounded during the Mardi Gras celebration in New Orleans.
Four people were wounded in an early morning shooting.

A shooter killed one and injured three after opening fire at a backyard party, after becoming upset, leaving and returning. He was chased down by partygoers who threw bricks at him in defense, and was pronounced dead by responding police.
Police responded to a shooting on Walnut Avenue, and found one teenager deceased and five adults injured.
Three women were killed and three police officers were wounded before a gunman killed himself in a murder–suicide in a home.
Two people were killed and four injured while standing on the sidewalk in the West Pullman area of the Far South Side.
Seven people were wounded at a candlelit vigil on the West Side for a hit and run victim. The shooter pulled up in a vehicle and opened fire on the crowd.
A boy and four others were wounded in a shooting in the Barry Farm neighborhood.
A gunman killed two people in a home and two other people in an apartment building before killing himself in a murder–suicide.
A man opened fire and others returned fire at a large party with at least one hundred people in attendance. Four people were injured in the shooting.

When responding to a hostage situation at a home in Wasco, officers were fired upon by the shooter. Two officers were shot, and one succumbed to their injuries. Three people inside the house were slain by the shooter. The gunman was also killed during the shootout.
Police discovered one person deceased and three injured after responding to reports of a shooting.
A man killed two people and injured three others in a series of shootings before being shot and killed by a police officer.
Fifteen people were injured, four critically, after a shooter opened fire at people leaving a funeral home in Chicago's Auburn Gresham neighborhood.
Five men were wounded shortly after midnight while standing in an Austin backyard, after a man entered and opened fire.
Multiple shooters reportedly opened fire at a block party, injuring five people.
A sheriff's deputy was killed and three detectives and a passerby were wounded in a shooting. The suspect was killed by police.
Five people were wounded in the North Lawndale neighborhood. They were a part of people gathered on the sidewalk when a car pulled up and several men got out and opened fire.
Two people were killed and three injured after someone opened fire on a group leaving a nightclub.
One teenager was killed and two women and a child were injured after being shot in a parking lot.
One person was killed and five others were injured in a shooting at a sports bar.
One man was killed and four others injured after a fight in a McDonald's parking lot escalated. One of the injured was an innocent bystander in the Food Lion parking lot across the street.
Four people were wounded in a parking lot in Short North in an early morning.
Several people were gathered outside of a party when a man opened fire, killing two and wounding three.
Three people in a car and a man standing at a bus stop were injured when they were shot at by someone in another vehicle.

Thirteen people were injured in an early morning shooting at a riverfront gathering. An argument between two women led to a man firing two shots into the air. This led to multiple individuals opening fire on the crowd.
Six people were wounded in an early morning shooting after an argument escalated at an after-hours club.
Five people were wounded in a parking lot, after an SUV pulled up and its occupants began shooting.
A man shot his ex-girlfriend and three other people at a car wash. The suspect also sustained a gunshot injury, suspected to be self-inflicted, and later died of his injuries.
Eight people including a fifteen-year-old girl were injured in a drive by shooting early in the morning.
Two people were killed and two injured shortly after midnight after a fight escalated.
Four people, including a teenager were found shot in McElderry Park.
Four men were killed in a shooting in an apartment.
Two people were killed and three wounded shortly before midnight in Morgan Park on the Far South Side. They were part of a group of people, that were fired upon by  an unknown shooter.

Two people were killed and four injured inside a parking garage near a local nightclub. Responding officers attempted to stop multiple vehicles leaving the structure, with some carrying shooting victims.
Police responded to a noise complaint at a large party, and discovered ten people with gunshot wounds. One later died from their injuries.
Two were killed and three people were injured in a shooting at a bar.
Police responding to reports of a shooting discovered one man killed and eight other adults wounded.
Two people were killed and two wounded in a drive-by-shooting.
Ten people were wounded in a shooting at a bar.
Five people were injured in a gang-related drive-by shooting.

Two fifteen-year-olds and two seventeen-year-olds were wounded while sitting in traffic when another car pulled up and opened fire. Four days later, the suspect was shot by police after a pursuit in which he was found holding a gun and died at a hospital.
Four people were wounded in a van after individuals in a pickup truck opened fire in the early morning.
One teenager was killed and five were injured in a shooting.
Four people were wounded in a fight in and outside a club.
A man opened fire in a restaurant, killing three men and injuring another. The shooter has been taken into custody.
One person was killed and five injured outside a local restaurant in a drive-by shooting.
Four people were injured in a shooting in the Hilltop neighborhood.
Four people were injured in a shooting.
A man was killed and four others wounded after two men opened fire in the early morning in the North Lawndale neighborhood. The men were standing on a street corner.
Ten minutes after an earlier shooting, three teenagers (two would later die) and two adults were wounded in North Lawndale.
A man opened fire on a group of people, killing two and wounding two others at an apartment complex.
Four people were injured in a drive-by shooting.
Four adults were wounded while attending a memorial in Weinland Park. A three-year-old girl was also wounded when bullets struck the home she was in.
A man was killed and four others wounded at a condo complex after an argument escalated.
Five people were wounded after gunfire erupted at a warehouse party.

Marshall County High School Shooting: A fifteen-year-old student killed two other students and injured sixteen others before discarding his weapon and attempting to hide among other students. He was apprehended by police.
Three adults and a child were injured after a man, out on bond from a January arrest, entered their home and opened fire.
A 15-year-old and a 16-year-old were killed and three other adults were wounded on a street corner. The 16-year-old died the next day.
One person was killed and five were injured in a shooting during a family dispute.
Four children were injured in a shooting. Two teenage suspects were arrested by police.
Eight or nine people opened fire in the early morning in a drive-by shooting. Five people were wounded, including a juvenile.
Shortly before midnight someone opened fire on a party bus passing by a gas station in Old Town. Seven people were wounded in the bus, and one while pumping gas.
Two people were killed and two were wounded after an assailant shot into a vehicle outside of a tobacco store.
Four people were injured after being shot near the entrance to a party.
Two gunmen opened fire in the early morning outside a Brooklyn apartment building. A man was killed and five other adults were wounded.
Four adults were killed in a robbery after three men broke into their home. The three men were arrested later the next day.
One person was killed and eight were wounded at a high school graduation party when a gunman opened fire during a fight.
A man killed one person and injured three others after determining them to be acquaintances of a person who stole his favorite pistol. The man was later taken into custody.
A man was killed and two adults and an 11-year-old child were injured after an argument escalated from an original argument at a basketball court.
Four men were injured in Homan Square while standing outside at night.
A 57-year-old woman was killed and five others were wounded during a vigil at a local bar.
Five people were injured in a gang-related drive-by shooting believed to be related to a murder that had happened the previous day. Two suspects were arrested.
Five men were injured while standing in a park after a vehicle drove by and opened fire.
A gunman opened fire at a group of people leaving a bar early in the morning. Six people were wounded.
One man was killed and five were wounded at an overnight block party.
One person was killed and four were injured in a shooting following a fight at a biker club party.
Six adults and two children aged four and eight-years-old were wounded after someone opened fire at a party outside a home.
One person was killed and three wounded in a shooting.
Seven people were wounded at a house party near the campus of Ball State University.
Four people were injured in a shooting at a hotel. A suspect was arrested.
Multiple shooters traveled across three different blocks and wounded six people in Brooklyn.
A man was killed and four others wounded in a drive by shooting outside of a convenience store.
A woman and three others, including a 4-year-old boy were wounded in what police presume was a targeted shooting. One of the victims later died from their injuries.
A man wounded his stepmother and killed her two daughters before highjacking a car, killing the driver and wounding the passenger. A suspect was arrested after abandoning the car.
A 16-year-old was killed and three others, including two juveniles, were wounded at a gas station.
Four were wounded in a shooting after an argument.
Four people, including two teenagers were wounded in a shooting.
Four people were discovered in a vehicle, two deceased and two wounded, after police responded to calls of an abandoned car.
Five adults and a teenager were wounded after an argument escalated at a Metro bus stop.

Two EMTs were injured after a man opened fire on them as they responded to an unrelated medical incident. The man then drove to a nearby structure fire and shot at nearby people, killing a bystander and wounding a firefighter.
Four people, including two children were wounded during an altercation between two men in a strip mall parking lot.
A shooting on US Highway 29 led to the shooting of another person at a local hospital. One person was killed and five others were wounded. Three suspects were arrested.

Two people were killed and three injured at a large outdoor hip hop concert in which potentially five separate guns were used. An additional three people were injured while attempting to flee, after being hit by cars.

Responding officers arrived at a motel where a man was threatening to kill others and responding officers. The man shot and killed two adults and wounded two others before being shot and killed by police.
Three people were killed and two were critically injured in a shooting at a home. One victim died of their injuries days later, taking the death toll to four.
Four people were wounded while leaving a private party.
A man was killed and seven others injured in an early morning shooting outside an Exxon gas station.
One person died and three were wounded after a shooting outside a nightclub.
Three men and a teenager were wounded in a drive-by shooting in the Central City neighborhood.
Six people were wounded in a drive-by shooting behind a bar.
Three women and two men were injured after someone opened fire outside an apartment complex. At the complex there was a large party happening with over 100 people present.
A woman was killed and six others were injured in a shooting in Downtown Portland.

A person began shooting at an event that was originally reported to be a rap concert and subsequently described as a birthday party. Four people were injured by the gunfire, and a fifth person suffered a head injury after falling.
A 33-year-old was killed and three others wounded in a common area of an apartment complex.
Two men opened fire on a late night cookout at the Raymond Bush Playground in Brooklyn. Three men were injured and an infant sitting in a stroller was killed.
Five teenage girls aged 12 to 19 years old were wounded while standing outside a party in Austin on the West Side.
Four people were wounded in a shooting inside of a residence. The perpetrator was later arrested.
A 21-year-old was killed and three others were wounded shortly after midnight at a New Year's Eve party.
Two men were killed in an early morning shooting at a party, with two others wounded.
Shortly before midnight two men were killed and four others injured in Old Sacramento near the old train tracks.
A shooting was reported near Farragut Elementary School, where two men were discovered wounded, and an additional four were identified at the hospital.
A man was killed and two other men and a woman were wounded in Englewood in the evening.
A six-year-old girl was killed and five adults were injured in a shooting in the nation's capital.
A large group of adult men were ambushed by three teenagers who came out of a breezeway and shot and injured five of them.
Four men were wounded and one killed in an early morning shooting. The group was standing in the street when a verbal altercation escalated with at least two shooters.
Four people were wounded as passengers in a van taking them from a nightclub.
Four people were wounded in a shooting near the northwest side of Indianapolis.
Responding officers to an early morning block party arrived to gunfire. Two wounded individuals were identified at the party and four others were identified at local hospitals.
One person was killed and three injured at Conestee Park after an argument escalated.

STEM School Highlands Ranch shooting: Authorities responded to the STEM School Highlands Ranch, at about 1:50 pm on a report of shots fired. One student was fatally shot and eight others were injured; two suspects were taken into custody by police.
Four teenagers aged between 15 and 13-years-old and 10-year-old child were wounded. Someone opened fire on a playground late at night.
One man was killed and three others injured in Austin shortly before midnight.
Just before 4 am, officers discovered one person deceased and four people wounded, after a fight potentially escalated.
In a late night shooting, four people were killed and three injured. Officers suspect the shooting was retaliation by people recently released from prison.
An adult was killed and three adults and a fourteen-year-old injured in an evening shooting.
Officers responded to a call and discovered six individuals wounded by gunfire; the victims were transported to local hospitals for treatment.
Shortly after midnight an individual stormed an apartment and wounded a man and four teenagers aged 14 to 19-years-old.
Officers responding to a ShotSpotter alert discovered four people wounded at the Bromley Heath Projects in Mission Hill.
Five people were shot inside of a vehicle; the incident resulted in one death and four injuries.
Shots were fired into a group of people in the Auburn Gresham area on the South Side. The evening shooting wounded six.
Officers responding to a 911 call were fired upon by a suspect who barricaded themselves in a home. One officer was killed and three injured.
Three teens and one man were injured after a fight involving between 20 and 30 individuals.
Two men were killed and four others - two men and two women - were injured in a shooting at a late-night party.
A man was killed and four others injured after an argument and physical fight between multiple motorcycle clubs escalated.
Four people were wounded in a shooting at West 27th and Tatnall Streets.
Three men waiting at a stop light and were wounded when someone opened fire. Comedian Rickey Smiley's daughter was a passenger in another vehicle and was also wounded.
Five adults were wounded outside a food mart in Gresham after three men jumped out of a car and opened fire.
Four people were injured and discovered after a Shot Spotter gunfire alert notified police to the location.
A 16-year-old girl and three adults were wounded by gunfire while standing in an alley in the West Side's Fifth City neighborhood in the early morning.
Five people were wounded in West Garfield Park on the West Side, after a man approached them and opened fire.
Emergency responders discovered a female and two young children injured, and two men were later identified as being wounded in the same incident.
Officers arrived at an early morning fight and heard shots being fired. They later discovered a man killed by the gunfire and three others injured.
A man and teenager were killed and two adults wounded in an evening shooting in the Knollwood neighborhood.
Four men were discovered shot at Cherrywood Park after a drive-by shooting; one of the victims died from their injuries.
At least two people are killed and eight injured, four critically, at a nightclub. No suspects have been arrested.
Four men were wounded in an early morning shooting, three of the four were found in a vehicle.
One person was killed and three were wounded while sitting in a parked car in Boston's Dorchester neighborhood.
Four adults and a 15-year-old boy were injured in an early morning shooting in Inwood, Manhattan.
A man was killed and six others wounded at a banquet hall, after a shooter opened fire due to an earlier argument. Attendees fired back and wounded the suspect, who was later arrested.

University of North Carolina at Charlotte shooting: Six people were shot, two fatally, on the last day of classes at the University of North Carolina at Charlotte. The student gunman was taken into custody after he was tackled by one of the students in the classroom. He had several more loaded magazines in a backpack.
A man was killed and three others injured in a parking lot, after leaving an event held by rapper Bankroll Freddie. People were leaving the event when someone fired into the crowd.
Four people were wounded in the early morning at a hotel.
Four family members, three women and one man, were found shot to death in an apartment. The suspect remains at large.
Shortly after midnight three men and one woman were injured.
Multiple masked shooters wounded four in Queens after exiting a car and opening fire.
Two men got into an altercation at a party and exchanged gunfire; seven people were wounded in the crossfire.
Four people were wounded in an early morning shooting, with potentially multiple weapons used.
Two men were killed and three injured after a gun fight between two cars in the parking lot of a housing complex.
A suspect in a vehicle opened fire on patrons outside of a nightclub, injuring four.
A large group of people were watching fireworks, when a fight broke out after a car hit a pedestrian. Fourteen people were wounded, of which two were declared dead at the hospital.
Three men were killed and one injured after a gunman opened fire at a house party.
One person was killed and seven were wounded when a gunman opened fire on two cookouts at an intersection.
A woman was killed and five men were wounded in an early morning drive-by shooting. The group was setting off fireworks when the car approached.
A man was killed and five others wounded at an activities complex in the early morning.
One person was killed and three were injured in a shooting in south Jackson.

A 20-year-old opened fire on a group of six people after getting into an altercation and taking a rifle from his father. Four of the group were injured and the 20-year-old and his father were arrested.
Six men were wounded after two shooters walked up to them and opened fire shortly before midnight in the North Philadelphia neighborhood of  Hunting Park.
Four people were wounded in an overnight shooting.
An adult and 11-year-old girl were killed shortly after midnight, three others were wounded. Officers believe that there were two shooters.
Four people were wounded in Dorchester, neighbors at first believed it was continuing Independence Day celebrations.
Poway synagogue shooting: One person was killed and at least three were wounded by a shooter at the Chabad of Poway synagogue.
Shortly after midnight a man was killed and five others were wounded.
A man was killed and a woman and two children were injured at a gas station in a potential incident of domestic violence.
Investigators attempted to make contact with the suspect in relation to another crime, he then began to open fire, injuring three children and himself.
Five teenagers were wounded shortly after midnight after a shooting occurred at a house party.
Four men were wounded by five teenagers who opened fire at the same location they had wounded a woman two days prior. The teenagers were later arrested.
Four people were wounded in the Grays Ferry Section of the city.
A group of people were traveling in a party bus, when someone opened fire on the vehicle. Four people in the bus were wounded.
Three adults and a three-year-old were injured while standing outside in a large group after someone opened fire.
Four seniors were wounded by gunfire after a suspect opened fire in the vehicle behind them.
Four men were wounded in Marlow Heights, one man later died at the hospital.
A drive-by shooting left one person dead and three others injured at an illegal fireworks show.
Seven people were wounded in a shooting that police believe occurred after a large fight.
Two adults and two children were injured in a drive-by shooting.
A shooting in Washington Park left two dead and four injured, including a 12-year-old girl and a 13-year-old boy.
A disturbance in a neighborhood escalated into a shooting; four men were wounded.
A group of people were fired at by an individual in a vehicle, shortly before midnight. Five people were wounded.
One person was killed and eleven others injured at an Independence Day block party.
Two suspects fired multiple shots at people attending a party, injuring four.
An early morning shooting occurred at a nightclub, after an altercation escalated. One person was killed and three others wounded.
An overnight shooting left four injured, two critically.
Four people in a vehicle were wounded when they were shot at by at least one person in another car.
A man was killed and three others injured in a late night shooting in South Chicago.
Two people were killed and three injured in a shooting at a large teen party at a city park.
A drive-by shooting killed an 18-year-old male and wounded three other men in a cul-de-sac.
Four people are killed, and at least four more were injured at an outdoor gathering in Englewood when four men opened fire into a crowd. No suspects have been arrested.
Four adults were wounded in an evening shooting.
A man opened fire inside of a bar following a disturbance, wounding four patrons.
A man was killed and four others injured at a July 4 cookout.
Two juveniles and two others were injured on Sunday night.
One man was killed and three were injured in an early morning shooting.
Four women were injured in a late night shooting in southwest Baltimore.
A group of people were fired upon in a parking lot, leaving one dead and four injured.
Two women were killed and another man and woman were wounded in a drive-by shooting outside of Miami's Liberty City neighborhood.
A suspected shootout occurred inside the Riverchase Galleria in the afternoon. An 8-year-old boy was killed and two adults and a girl were injured.
Four people were wounded in a shooting at a rap concert.
Four people were injured in a shooting outside of a restaurant and bar.
A group of five were shot after a man got out of a vehicle and opened fire. Two girls were killed aged 11 and 12-years-old and three adults were wounded.
Four adults were wounded at a local club, and all refused to talk with law enforcement about the incident.

A man killed his wife, two of his daughters, and another man, and injured two people who came to try to help one of the victims. All of the victims were shot, with the exception of one of his daughters who was killed by blunt force trauma.
A man and three women were wounded in a late night shooting, the next day three suspects were arrested.
Eight people were wounded near a local car wash in the early morning.
One person was killed and four were wounded when suspects fired at them from a car in the Watts neighborhood of Los Angeles.
A man was killed and four others injured shortly after midnight on a street corner.
Two juveniles and three adults were wounded in a shooting.
Four men were wounded in a shooting near Druid Hill Park.
Three men and a woman were wounded in their vehicle on Interstate 580.
A shooting at an Independence Day gathering in southeast Dallas left at least four people wounded.
Police found four people with gunshot wounds in front of a residence.
Officers responding to a call of shots fired discovered four wounded individuals. A man later died at the hospital.
A shooting at a neighborhood block party left three people dead and two injured.
Four people were wounded in a shooting at a mobile home park.
Five men were wounded in an evening shooting. Officers believed the shooting was targeted at the group.
Responding officers found three men killed and one injured at a large party in the early morning.
Two people were killed and three were wounded in a shooting at a motorcycle club hangout.
Early in the morning, a group of men sitting on the sidewalk were shot at in a drive-by. One man was killed and four injured.
Four adults were wounded in an early morning shooting.
Six people were wounded in a shooting outside of a local bar.
Shortly after midnight three men and a woman were shot while waiting in a vehicle at a Shell gas station in River North neighborhood. The shooter was in and later fled in a red sedan.
One person was killed and three injured in a shooting at a sports bar.
Six young men were wounded in a shooting in the city's East Side district.
Three men and one women were all wounded in a shooting.
Shortly before midnight four men were wounded in a drive-by shooting in Gresham.
At least six people were injured in a shooting at a baby shower.
Three adults and one juvenile were wounded, after going to a residence and getting into an altercation. The shooter was a juvenile resident of the home.
A man was killed and four others injured after an afternoon shooting in East Mount Airy.
Four Florida A&M University students were injured in a shooting following an argument at a house party.
Four men were wounded in a public park in Sylmar in a drive-by shooting.
Three teenagers and a six-year-old were injured in an afternoon shooting. A fifteen-year-old was later arrested in connection with the shooting.
One person was killed and three were found with gunshot injuries in Panama City.
A man shot and killed another man in a home, after mistaking it as the home of his intended target. He left and entered the correct home and wounded three others.
A teenager was killed and four adults, including a pregnant woman were injured at an American Legion after a funeral.
Two officers responding to a suspected hostage situation were wounded and three individuals were later found deceased in a murder–suicide.
Two men were killed and two injured in a late night shooting in the Kensington neighborhood.
Unknown assailants fired into a residence in Englewood, injuring seven people including a baby girl.
A man shot four people in a drive-by shooting outside of a convenience store.
During an early morning field party, seven people were wounded after an argument between two men escalated.
Two people, including the believed shooter, were killed and four injured in a shooting at a local park.
Five people were wounded in a drive-by shooting at an intersection.
Red Bluff shooting. An employee was killed and four injured at a Walmart distribution center. The perpetrator was later killed in a shootout with responding police.
Responding police officers to shots fired, found one man deceased and an adult and two teenagers injured.
One person was killed and four people were wounded in a shooting in East Garfield Park.
Officers responding to an early morning ShotSpotter alert found two men wounded and identified two women who arrived at the hospital to be a part of the incident.
Four teenagers were wounded while walking in Little Village on the West Side in the evening.
One person was killed and four were wounded during a house party.
Early in the morning a man opened fire at a house party in Brooklyn, and injured four people.
A car pulled up to another car waiting to turn and opened fire. An adult, ten-month-old, four and fifteen-year olds were all injured.
Seven people were wounded in a shooting at an overnight house party.
A man was killed and three others wounded after a large gathering in Douglas.
A group of people were fired upon, leaving one killed and three injured.
Four people were wounded in a shooting near a playground.

A Missouri man traveled to the area for a house party, where a couple got into a physical domestic fight. Shortly after 911 was called in response to that fight the man opened fire and killed his Uncle and two others, and wounded another.
Two adults and a six-year-old were killed and a ten-year-old injured in an evening shooting.
An after-school fight led to a shooting in a neighborhood; five teenagers were wounded.
Five people were wounded by a shooter outside a local grocery store. Officers previously thought the incident was a gunfight but later announced it was one shooter.
A man opened fire into a crowded Walmart parking lot, killing one and injuring three.
A shooting occurred near the Fillmore Heritage Center around 8:40 pm local time; one person was killed and five others were injured.
Four people were wounded at a house party shortly before midnight, after two shooters appeared near a neighboring home.
A man was killed and three others wounded at a night club in the early morning.
During a warehouse party, a fight broke out and escalated into a shooting; seven people were wounded.
Three adults and a 14-year-old boy were wounded in the early morning at a gas station. Prior to the shooting, a large crowd of people and cars had been gathered around the gas station.
A woman died and ten others were injured after three shooters approached them from an alley and opened fire in Marquette Park.
An argument at a house party ended in a shooting when the perpetrator returned to the party and killed two and wounded four before fleeing.
Four men were wounded after a shooting at an intersection in the Kensington neighborhood.
Five adults and a teenager were wounded in a drive-by shooting while standing outside in South Shore. A woman died later at the hospital
Four people were wounded after an argument, although the shooter claims that it was in self-defense to being randomly attacked.
A man was killed, and two adults and a 17-year-old injured while attempting to make a rap music video. Officers believed the shooting was targeted, as the victims refused to cooperate.
A tenant with a mental disorder killed three and wounded a neighbor in his boarding house.
Four people were wounded at the El Cortez Hotel and Casino in an early morning shooting. The suspect was later arrested.
Three adults and one juvenile were wounded in an early morning shooting. The suspected shooter was arrested.
After an argument escalated at a pool party hosted at an apartment complex, four people were wounded.
In the early morning, two groups were involved in a dispute, which ended with one person killed and three people wounded.
Four people were wounded in a drive by shooting in Burnside, while standing on a porch.
A man was killed and three wounded at a pay-per-view event at a nightclub after a fight broke out.
One man was killed and three others were wounded following a shooting at a "residential speakeasy".
Five people were wounded in a drive-by shooting during the evening. Responding police believed the shooter and victims know each other.
A man was killed and three others wounded after an argument escalated in the morning in West Rogers Park.
Two men were killed and three others were wounded in an overnight shooting behind a home. The suspect was arrested the next day.
Police discovered five men wounded by gunfire in the Tenderloin neighborhood.
An argument escalated at a funeral service after an outside group refused to turn down music in their car. A man was killed and three others injured.
One person was fatally shot and three others were wounded, including a Montana Highway Patrol trooper following a road rage incident.

Officers responding to a block party on reports of someone being hit by a car arrived to shots being fired. Three people were killed and six injured by gunfire, with an additional five injured after being hit by cars while attempting to flee.
Two children and two adults were shot in an SUV.
One person was killed and three were wounded after gunfire erupted in a nightclub.
Officers responding to a shooting on West Broadway Avenue discovered four people injured.
Shortly before midnight, two men and two women were injured in a drive-by shooting in Park Manor, in which the shooter drove a moped.
Four men were wounded in a shooting inside of a local liquor store.
Four people were wounded in the Willard-Hay neighborhood during the afternoon.
Five people were shot in an early morning drive-by at a graduation party in the Bronx.
A conflict between two individuals escalated into a shooting; one man was killed, and four others were injured.
Five people were wounded in a drive-by, including a 16-year-old girl, at an early morning gathering in East Garfield Park.
Two shooters opened fire at a local American Legion Post, which was hosting a teen party. All five injured were teenagers.
Three children and one adult were wounded in a drive-by shooting.
Four people were wounded early in the morning after an individual opened fire from a vehicle in the Back of the Yards neighborhood on the South Side.
Two adults and two children were wounded at the local JFK Park, after a man opened fire.
Four people were injured in a shooting at a sports bar following a fight.
Five people were shot during a vigil in the Crown Heights area of Brooklyn in the evening.
Four people were shot while standing outside when two shooters opened fire in South Austin.
Six people were injured in a shooting at a bar following a fight.
Four men were wounded after a shooting at an early morning gathering of cars.
Two men were found dead and two more injured by responding police officers.
One person was killed and four other were wounded at a party when shots were fired into a home.
Five people were wounded in an early morning shooting.
Four motorcycle club members were wounded in Englewood.
Two adults and their 6 and 1-year-old children were killed in an apparent murder suicide.
Early in the morning a shooting occurred at a house party. Five individuals were shot and one died on the way to the hospital in a private vehicle.
Minnesota Vikings defensive tackle Jaylen Twyman was shot along with three others while visiting his aunt.
One person was killed and four others were wounded in a shooting near a gas station.
Shortly after midnight, officers responded to a home after a complaint of gunshots. They discovered four men wounded.
Three people were killed and four injured in a shooting outside a convenience store.
Two people were killed and two were injured in a shooting at a party in a home.
An argument in Humboldt Park escalated shortly after midnight. A man was killed and three wounded.
A man was killed and three wounded while leaving Shockoe Bottom after someone opened fire on a group of people.
Two people were killed and two others were found wounded in two separate shootings believed to be perpetrated by the same man.
A group of people fired into a crowd, killing one and injuring 11 others.
A woman was killed and three others injured shortly after midnight.
Officers on patrol responded to gunshots, and upon investigation discovered a deceased male and four wounded victims.
Officers arrived at a large party in a public parking lot after reports of a stolen car was made. An individual opened fire as they arrived and injured nine people including a 17-year-old.
A man was killed and four others wounded during an early morning Juneteenth celebration at a local strip mall.
A gunman perched on the roof of a home killed two and wounded two after an argument led to the incident.
Three women and a man were injured after a fight broke out between two groups gathered at Claremont park.
A woman was killed and ten others injured at an annual community Fathers Day celebration. The shooter was shortly arrested.
Three adults and a teenager were injured inside a home in a presumed targeted shooting.
Four people were wounded in a drive-by shooting in the evening.
Celebrators of a Marimba; a Guatemalan music and dance party, were shot by multiple shooters who fled in vehicles
A 28-year-old woman killed her three children, ages 8, 6 and 2, before killing herself.
A woman sitting in her car was killed and three others injured in a separate car early in the morning. A shoot-out had occurred in a large gathering nearby.
Eight people were wounded in a shootout between two groups after an argument escalated. Each group had rented a party space, and two of the injured were children.
Five people were wounded after shots were fired outside of a bar. Two suspects were taken into custody by police.
Early in the morning two people were killed and two wounded in a shooting.
A man was killed and four others were wounded in an early morning shooting at a local brewing companies parking lot.
Two people were wounded and two were killed in a shooting at an apartment complex. The suspect was later arrested in Bienville Parish, Louisiana.
One person was killed and four injured shortly after midnight.
One man was killed and three others injured while standing on a porch after a bicyclist opened fire.
After police attempted to arrest a suspect, a gunfight broke out, and led to one person being killed and five being wounded.
Five people were shot at a motel after a party in one of the rooms had an argument that escalated. Police believe the shooting was intended to be targeted.
A man was killed and five others injured at Lake Merritt near the city's Juneteenth celebration.

Police responded to a domestic dispute at a residence; upon arrival, the suspect fired shots at officers leading to a 12-hour hostage standoff. Four people were killed, and the suspect was taken into custody and later died.
Four people were wounded at an overnight park party in the Bronx after an argument escalated.
Four people wounded and one killed in a shooting.
Aurora, Illinois shooting: A man opened fire in his workplace, killing five employees, and injuring five police officers and a civilian before being killed by police.
Officers responding to a shots fired call in the early morning found four people wounded at an adult entertainment venue.
Two people were killed and four injured in a parking lot after an argument escalated between unknown people and partygoers leaving a concert.
After a fight broke out near a basketball court at a park, multiple people started shooting at each other. Two people were killed, and two were wounded.

Early in the morning a man was discovered by officers with a gunshot wound. Shortly after transporting the man to the hospital, six other victims were identified at local hospitals to be a part of the same shooting.
Responding officers found two wounded men in an early morning shooting. Shortly after two more were identified at a local hospital.
A family member heard sounds of gunfire, and upon investigation, found four adults and one toddler deceased.

Three adults and a nine-year-old child were wounded while standing in an apartment complex parking lot in the Gresham neighborhood. A man walked up and opened fire on the group, resulting in a shoot out.
Shortly before midnight five people were wounded in Dinkytown.
Four people were injured in a shooting outside of an apartment complex.
In an apparent shoot out at a birthday party, one man was killed and two women injured. A second man died in his vehicle while attempting to drive away from the scene with a gunshot wound.
A shooting killed two and wounded another two.
A man was killed and three others were injured after a shooting in the lobby of an apartment building around 10:30 pm ET.
An early morning shooting during a block party injured four people. The suspected shooter was arrested after a local traffic stop.
Four men were wounded in a shooting.
One man was killed and three others were injured after a shooting broke out in Cleveland's Clark–Fulton neighborhood.
A 15-year-old and three adults were gathered outside an apartment when they were injured in a drive-by shooting in the Montclare neighborhood.
Four people were wounded in a shooting.
A man and woman were killed and two others injured after the shooter kicked open an apartment door and shot inside, before fleeing.
Early in the morning six people were wounded and one was killed in an incident. Officers were alerted via a ShotSpotter activation.

One person was killed and twelve others injured in eight drive-by shootings in the West Valley area. A male suspect was taken into custody. Of the injuries, three were wounded by gunfire, while nine others sustained indirect injuries, such as shrapnel from broken glass due to a car crash.
Four men and an elementary-school-age girl were injured in a shooting at a bus stop.
About 100 people were gathered at a skate park in the early morning when someone opened fire. One person was killed and four injured.
Six people were shot, one fatally, in West Baltimore.
Four people were wounded in an early morning shooting.
Four people were wounded in an early morning shooting at a local night club. A suspected shooter was arrested.
Five people were wounded at West Garfield Park.
Around 2 am local time, two people were killed and five people were wounded in a drive-by shooting after a fight outside of a club.
Officers responded to an early morning shooting and found five people wounded. All but one were transported to local hospitals.
Four women were killed and three others injured after gunfire erupted in a South Side residence. Another woman died in a hospital.
A fight broke out at a house party and shots were fired; four people were wounded.
One man was killed and three others injured during the evening.
A shooting at a Mueller Water Products factory killed two and injured two others.
Pecan Park Raid: Four police officers were shot while serving a warrant in southeast Houston. The two homeowners were killed.
Over 100 people attended a house party when someone opened fire, injuring five people.
A drive-by shooting on Interstate 95 killed one and injured three.
Police responded to a call and discovered five people with gunshot wounds, along with two of the victims sustaining life-threatening injuries.
Shortly before midnight, four individuals were wounded in a shooting.
Two people were killed and two others injured at a city park.
A gunman opened fire on individuals attending a candlelight vigil, killing one, and wounding three others.
Five individuals were wounded and one killed during an early morning shooting in the JeffVanderLou neighborhood.
An altercation resulted in a shooting that killed one and injured five others at a racetrack.
A man was asked to leave a bar; shortly after, he came back and shot five people, critically wounding two.
One person was killed and seven others wounded after a shooting at a house party. Local police believe the incident is gang related.
One man was killed and three other people were injured after a shooting in a Newburg neighborhood.
Two people were found with bullet wounds in front of a residence, and two more arrived at a hospital with gunshot injuries from the same shooting.
An individual shot at a large group of people from a vehicle, killing two people and wounding five.
Four people were wounded in a drive-by. Two of the victims were children caught in crossfire.
January 2019 Louisiana shootings: A 21-year-old man killed five people, including his parents, in two parishes in Louisiana. The suspect fled to Virginia and was arrested the next day.
Five people were wounded in the Fells Point neighborhood during a large gathering at Broadway Square with many of the crowd drinking alcoholic drinks.
A shooting in Chatham on the South Side left one dead and nine injured.
A man killed two people and injured one inside a local bar, then drove away and broke into a home and killed the homeowner before killing himself.
Shortly before midnight responding officers discovered seven shooting victims. A man and woman later died at local hospitals with five other men wounded.
Three men were killed while three women and another man were injured in the Kinsman neighborhood.
A man killed four individuals and injured another in two separate shootings.
Early in the morning five men and one woman were wounded after multiple men opened fire on a group in the Tioga neighborhood, causing the group to scatter and run away.
At least 14 people were shot in Downtown Austin in the early morning hours, leaving one dead. A suspect has been arrested while police are still looking for another.
2019 Sebring shooting: At least five people were killed in a hostage incident and shooting at a bank. The suspect was taken into custody by police.
A 19-year-old woman was killed and a man and a two teenagers wounded at a local park in the Bronx late at night.
A shooting left five people injured, including a four-year-old girl.
Three adults and a child were wounded in a shooting while attending a block party.
A man denied entry into a bar for being too drunk, stated "Don't you know who I am?" to the bouncer before leaving. He returned later with a rifle and opened fire injuring five women and three men.
A shooting left one man dead and four others injured.
One person was killed and four others were wounded in a shooting at a nightclub.
Shortly after midnight responding officers discovered two men wounded by gunfire. Another man and a woman were taken to the hospital in private vehicles.
One person was killed and seven others wounded in a shooting at a housing project.
A man killed two people and injured two more before killing himself.
A mother killed her neighbor, and four children aged 12, 8, and 5-years-old and a 5-month-old infant, before committing suicide in a murder-suicide.
Two people were killed and two others hurt in a shooting in White Center near West Seattle.
In an apparent targeted shooting, four individuals were discovered shot in a building.
Seven people including two juveniles were wounded in the Trinidad neighborhood of DC. Officers discovered the victims after hearing gunshots in the early morning.
A drive by shooting on the west side left one dead and three injured, including a six-year-old boy.
Early in the morning, three women and a man were involved in a fight and were injured in the ensuing shooting.
Two men were killed, and three men and a 13-year-old were wounded in a drive-by shooting while standing in an apartment complex parking lot.
Four people were wounded in a drive by shooting that was potential gang activity.
Three people were killed and two more were injured by a homeowner in a possible attempted home invasion.
Shortly before midnight, officers discovered three adults men and one juvenile boy wounded by gunfire. One adult man died later at the hospital.
Four people were wounded and one killed in an afternoon shooting. The suspect is known to the victims.
Three people were killed and another person was wounded in a shooting at a home. Two men were arrested in relation to the shooting.
A man shot and killed an individual and wounded an officer, responding officers killed the suspect and three officers were wounded after a short manhunt.

Three teenagers were wounded and an adult woman was killed after their cars were boxed in by other vehicles and fired upon. A fourth teenager was injured in a car accident as one of the cars attempted to flee the gunfire.

A man was killed and five other people were injured in a shooting. The Mayor of Jacksonville described the shooting as gang-related, although this characterization has been disputed by the sister of the deceased man.
Early in the morning ShotSpotter alerts caused officers to respond to a graduation party. One 18-year-old was killed and with three others wounded.
Four people were shot, and a fifth wounded by bullet fragments in the early morning at a bar. The shooting was believed to be in retaliation of three men being denied entry into the bar.
Three people were killed and another one was wounded in a shooting.
